var book = {
	"name": "1 Chronicles",
	"numChapters": 29,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span>Adam,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10254A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10254A\"></sup> Seth, Enosh,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Kenan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10255B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10255B\"></sup> Mahalalel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10255C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10255C\"></sup> Jared,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10255D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10255D\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Enoch,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10256E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10256E\"></sup> Methuselah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10256F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10256F\"></sup> Lamech,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10256G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10256G\"></sup> Noah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10256H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10256H\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The sons of Noah:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10257I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10257I\"></sup>Shem, Ham and Japheth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10257J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10257J\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The sons of Japheth:Gomer, Magog, Madai, Javan, Tubal, Meshek and Tiras.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The sons of Gomer:Ashkenaz, Riphath and Togarmah.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The sons of Javan:Elishah, Tarshish, the Kittites and the Rodanites.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The sons of Ham:Cush, Egypt, Put and Canaan.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The sons of Cush:Seba, Havilah, Sabta, Raamah and Sabteka.The sons of Raamah:Sheba and Dedan.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Cush was the father ofNimrod, who became a mighty warrior on earth.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Egypt was the father ofthe Ludites, Anamites, Lehabites, Naphtuhites,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Pathrusites, Kasluhites (from whom the Philistines came) and Caphtorites.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Canaan was the father ofSidon his firstborn, and of the Hittites,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Jebusites, Amorites, Girgashites,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Hivites, Arkites, Sinites,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Arvadites, Zemarites and Hamathites.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The sons of Shem:Elam, Ashur, Arphaxad, Lud and Aram.The sons of Aram:Uz, Hul, Gether and Meshek.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Arphaxad was the father of Shelah,and Shelah the father of Eber.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Two sons were born to Eber:One was named Peleg, because in his time the earth was divided; his brother was named Joktan.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Joktan was the father ofAlmodad, Sheleph, Hazarmaveth, Jerah,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Hadoram, Uzal, Diklah,",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Obal, Abimael, Sheba,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Ophir, Havilah and Jobab. All these were sons of Joktan.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Shem,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10277N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10277N\"></sup> Arphaxad, Shelah,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Eber, Peleg, Reu,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Serug, Nahor, Terah",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>and Abram (that is, Abraham).",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>The sons of Abraham:Isaac and Ishmael.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>These were their descendants:Nebaioth the firstborn of Ishmael, Kedar, Adbeel, Mibsam,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Mishma, Dumah, Massa, Hadad, Tema,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Jetur, Naphish and Kedemah. These were the sons of Ishmael.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>The sons born to Keturah, Abraham’s concubine:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10285Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10285Q\"></sup>Zimran, Jokshan, Medan, Midian, Ishbak and Shuah.The sons of Jokshan:Sheba and Dedan.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10285R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10285R\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>The sons of Midian:Ephah, Epher, Hanok, Abida and Eldaah.All these were descendants of Keturah.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Abraham<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10287T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10287T\"></sup> was the father of Isaac.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10287U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10287U\"></sup>The sons of Isaac:Esau and Israel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10287V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10287V\"></sup>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>The sons of Esau:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10288W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10288W\"></sup>Eliphaz, Reuel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10288X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10288X\"></sup> Jeush, Jalam and Korah.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>The sons of Eliphaz:Teman, Omar, Zepho, Gatam and Kenaz;by Timna: Amalek.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10289Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10289Y\"></sup>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>The sons of Reuel:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10290Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10290Z\"></sup>Nahath, Zerah, Shammah and Mizzah.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>The sons of Seir:Lotan, Shobal, Zibeon, Anah, Dishon, Ezer and Dishan.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>The sons of Lotan:Hori and Homam. Timna was Lotan’s sister.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>The sons of Shobal:Alvan, Manahath, Ebal, Shepho and Onam.The sons of Zibeon:Aiah and Anah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10293AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10293AB\"></sup>",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>The son of Anah:Dishon.The sons of Dishon:Hemdan, Eshban, Ithran and Keran.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>The sons of Ezer:Bilhan, Zaavan and Akan.The sons of Dishan:Uz and Aran.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>These were the kings who reigned in Edom before any Israelite king reigned:Bela son of Beor, whose city was named Dinhabah.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>When Bela died, Jobab son of Zerah from Bozrah succeeded him as king.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>When Jobab died, Husham from the land of the Temanites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10298AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10298AD\"></sup> succeeded him as king.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>When Husham died, Hadad son of Bedad, who defeated Midian in the country of Moab, succeeded him as king. His city was named Avith.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>When Hadad died, Samlah from Masrekah succeeded him as king.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>When Samlah died, Shaul from Rehoboth on the river succeeded him as king.",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>When Shaul died, Baal-Hanan son of Akbor succeeded him as king.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>When Baal-Hanan died, Hadad succeeded him as king. His city was named Pau, and his wife’s name was Mehetabel daughter of Matred, the daughter of Me-Zahab.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>Hadad also died.The chiefs of Edom were:Timna, Alvah, Jetheth,",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>Oholibamah, Elah, Pinon,",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>Kenaz, Teman, Mibzar,",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>Magdiel and Iram. These were the chiefs of Edom."
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span>These were the sons of Israel:Reuben, Simeon, Levi, Judah, Issachar, Zebulun,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Dan, Joseph, Benjamin, Naphtali, Gad and Asher.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The sons of Judah:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10310C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10310C\"></sup>Er, Onan and Shelah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10310D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10310D\"></sup> These three were born to him by a Canaanite woman, the daughter of Shua.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10310E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10310E\"></sup> Er, Judah’s firstborn, was wicked in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s sight; so the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> put him to death.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10310F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10310F\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Judah’s daughter-in-law<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10311G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10311G\"></sup> Tamar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10311H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10311H\"></sup> bore Perez<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10311I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10311I\"></sup> and Zerah to Judah. He had five sons in all.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The sons of Perez:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10312J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10312J\"></sup>Hezron<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10312K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10312K\"></sup> and Hamul.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The sons of Zerah:Zimri, Ethan, Heman, Kalkol and Darda—five in all.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The son of Karmi:Achar,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10314L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10314L\"></sup> who brought trouble on Israel by violating the ban on taking devoted things.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10314M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10314M\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The son of Ethan:Azariah.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The sons born to Hezron<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10316N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10316N\"></sup> were:Jerahmeel, Ram and Caleb.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Ram<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10317O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10317O\"></sup> was the father ofAmminadab<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10317P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10317P\"></sup>, and Amminadab the father of Nahshon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10317Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10317Q\"></sup> the leader of the people of Judah.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Nahshon was the father of Salmon, Salmon the father of Boaz,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Boaz<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10319R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10319R\"></sup> the father of Obed and Obed the father of Jesse.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10319S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10319S\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Jesse<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10320T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10320T\"></sup> was the father ofEliab<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10320U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10320U\"></sup> his firstborn; the second son was Abinadab, the third Shimea,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>the fourth Nethanel, the fifth Raddai,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>the sixth Ozem and the seventh David.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Their sisters were Zeruiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10323V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10323V\"></sup> and Abigail. Zeruiah’s<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10323W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10323W\"></sup> three sons were Abishai, Joab<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10323X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10323X\"></sup> and Asahel.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Abigail was the mother of Amasa,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10324Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10324Y\"></sup> whose father was Jether the Ishmaelite.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Caleb son of Hezron had children by his wife Azubah (and by Jerioth). These were her sons: Jesher, Shobab and Ardon.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>When Azubah died, Caleb<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10326Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10326Z\"></sup> married Ephrath, who bore him Hur.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Hur was the father of Uri, and Uri the father of Bezalel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10327AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10327AA\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Later, Hezron, when he was sixty years old, married the daughter of Makir the father of Gilead.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10328AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10328AB\"></sup> He made love to her, and she bore him Segub.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Segub was the father of Jair, who controlled twenty-three towns in Gilead.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>(But Geshur and Aram captured Havvoth Jair,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10330AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10330AC\"></sup> as well as Kenath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10330AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10330AD\"></sup> with its surrounding settlements—sixty towns.) All these were descendants of Makir the father of Gilead.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>After Hezron died in Caleb Ephrathah, Abijah the wife of Hezron bore him Ashhur<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10331AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10331AE\"></sup> the father of Tekoa.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>The sons of Jerahmeel the firstborn of Hezron:Ram his firstborn, Bunah, Oren, Ozem and Ahijah.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Jerahmeel had another wife, whose name was Atarah; she was the mother of Onam.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The sons of Ram the firstborn of Jerahmeel:Maaz, Jamin and Eker.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>The sons of Onam:Shammai and Jada.The sons of Shammai:Nadab and Abishur.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Abishur’s wife was named Abihail, who bore him Ahban and Molid.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>The sons of Nadab:Seled and Appaim. Seled died without children.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>The son of Appaim:Ishi, who was the father of Sheshan.Sheshan was the father of Ahlai.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>The sons of Jada, Shammai’s brother:Jether and Jonathan. Jether died without children.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>The sons of Jonathan:Peleth and Zaza.These were the descendants of Jerahmeel.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Sheshan had no sons—only daughters.He had an Egyptian servant named Jarha.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Sheshan gave his daughter in marriage to his servant Jarha, and she bore him Attai.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Attai was the father of Nathan,Nathan the father of Zabad,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10343AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10343AF\"></sup>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Zabad the father of Ephlal,Ephlal the father of Obed,",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Obed the father of Jehu,Jehu the father of Azariah,",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Azariah the father of Helez,Helez the father of Eleasah,",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Eleasah the father of Sismai,Sismai the father of Shallum,",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Shallum the father of Jekamiah,and Jekamiah the father of Elishama.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>The sons of Caleb<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10349AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10349AG\"></sup> the brother of Jerahmeel:Mesha his firstborn, who was the father of Ziph, and his son Mareshah, who was the father of Hebron.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>The sons of Hebron:Korah, Tappuah, Rekem and Shema.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Shema was the father of Raham, and Raham the father of Jorkeam. Rekem was the father of Shammai.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>The son of Shammai was Maon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10352AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10352AH\"></sup>, and Maon was the father of Beth Zur.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10352AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10352AI\"></sup>",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>Caleb’s concubine Ephah was the mother of Haran, Moza and Gazez. Haran was the father of Gazez.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>The sons of Jahdai:Regem, Jotham, Geshan, Pelet, Ephah and Shaaph.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>Caleb’s concubine Maakah was the mother of Sheber and Tirhanah.",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>She also gave birth to Shaaph the father of Madmannah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10356AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10356AJ\"></sup> and to Sheva the father of Makbenah and Gibea. Caleb’s daughter was Aksah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10356AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10356AK\"></sup>",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>These were the descendants of Caleb.The sons of Hur<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10357AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10357AL\"></sup> the firstborn of Ephrathah:Shobal the father of Kiriath Jearim,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10357AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10357AM\"></sup>",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>Salma the father of Bethlehem, and Hareph the father of Beth Gader.",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>The descendants of Shobal the father of Kiriath Jearim were:Haroeh, half the Manahathites,",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>and the clans of Kiriath Jearim: the Ithrites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10360AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10360AN\"></sup> Puthites, Shumathites and Mishraites. From these descended the Zorathites and Eshtaolites.",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>The descendants of Salma:Bethlehem, the Netophathites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10361AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10361AO\"></sup> Atroth Beth Joab, half the Manahathites, the Zorites,",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>and the clans of scribes who lived at Jabez: the Tirathites, Shimeathites and Sucathites. These are the Kenites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10362AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10362AP\"></sup> who came from Hammath,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10362AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10362AQ\"></sup> the father of the Rekabites.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10362AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10362AR\"></sup>"
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span>These were the sons of David<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10363C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10363C\"></sup> born to him in Hebron:The firstborn was Amnon the son of Ahinoam<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10363D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10363D\"></sup> of Jezreel;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10363E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10363E\"></sup>the second, Daniel the son of Abigail<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10363F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10363F\"></sup> of Carmel;",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>the third, Absalom the son of Maakah daughter of Talmai king of Geshur;the fourth, Adonijah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10364G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10364G\"></sup> the son of Haggith;",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>the fifth, Shephatiah the son of Abital;and the sixth, Ithream, by his wife Eglah.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>These six were born to David in Hebron,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10366H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10366H\"></sup> where he reigned seven years and six months.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10366I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10366I\"></sup>David reigned in Jerusalem thirty-three years,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and these were the children born to him there:Shammua, Shobab, Nathan and Solomon. These four were by Bathsheba<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10367J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10367J\"></sup> daughter of Ammiel.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>There were also Ibhar, Elishua, Eliphelet,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Nogah, Nepheg, Japhia,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Elishama, Eliada and Eliphelet—nine in all.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>All these were the sons of David, besides his sons by his concubines. And Tamar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10371K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10371K\"></sup> was their sister.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10371L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10371L\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Solomon’s son was Rehoboam,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10372M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10372M\"></sup>Abijah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10372N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10372N\"></sup> his son,Asa<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10372O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10372O\"></sup> his son,Jehoshaphat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10372P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10372P\"></sup> his son,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Jehoram<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10373Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10373Q\"></sup> his son,Ahaziah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10373R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10373R\"></sup> his son,Joash<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10373S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10373S\"></sup> his son,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Amaziah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10374T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10374T\"></sup> his son,Azariah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10374U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10374U\"></sup> his son,Jotham<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10374V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10374V\"></sup> his son,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Ahaz<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10375W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10375W\"></sup> his son,Hezekiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10375X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10375X\"></sup> his son,Manasseh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10375Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10375Y\"></sup> his son,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Amon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10376Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10376Z\"></sup> his son,Josiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10376AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10376AA\"></sup> his son.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The sons of Josiah:Johanan the firstborn,Jehoiakim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10377AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10377AB\"></sup> the second son,Zedekiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10377AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10377AC\"></sup> the third,Shallum<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10377AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10377AD\"></sup> the fourth.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The successors of Jehoiakim:Jehoiachin<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10378AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10378AE\"></sup> his son,and Zedekiah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10378AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10378AF\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The descendants of Jehoiachin the captive:Shealtiel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10379AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10379AG\"></sup> his son,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Malkiram, Pedaiah, Shenazzar,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10380AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10380AH\"></sup> Jekamiah, Hoshama and Nedabiah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10380AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10380AI\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The sons of Pedaiah:Zerubbabel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10381AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10381AJ\"></sup> and Shimei.The sons of Zerubbabel:Meshullam and Hananiah.Shelomith was their sister.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>There were also five others:Hashubah, Ohel, Berekiah, Hasadiah and Jushab-Hesed.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The descendants of Hananiah:Pelatiah and Jeshaiah, and the sons of Rephaiah, of Arnan, of Obadiah and of Shekaniah.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The descendants of Shekaniah:Shemaiah and his sons:Hattush,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10384AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10384AK\"></sup> Igal, Bariah, Neariah and Shaphat—six in all.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The sons of Neariah:Elioenai, Hizkiah and Azrikam—three in all.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The sons of Elioenai:Hodaviah, Eliashib, Pelaiah, Akkub, Johanan, Delaiah and Anani—seven in all."
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span>The descendants of Judah:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10387A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10387A\"></sup>Perez, Hezron,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10387B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10387B\"></sup> Karmi, Hur and Shobal.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Reaiah son of Shobal was the father of Jahath, and Jahath the father of Ahumai and Lahad. These were the clans of the Zorathites.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>These were the sons of Etam:Jezreel, Ishma and Idbash. Their sister was named Hazzelelponi.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Penuel was the father of Gedor, and Ezer the father of Hushah.These were the descendants of Hur,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10390C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10390C\"></sup> the firstborn of Ephrathah and father of Bethlehem.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10390D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10390D\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Ashhur<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10391E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10391E\"></sup> the father of Tekoa had two wives, Helah and Naarah.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Naarah bore him Ahuzzam, Hepher, Temeni and Haahashtari. These were the descendants of Naarah.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The sons of Helah:Zereth, Zohar, Ethnan,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>and Koz, who was the father of Anub and Hazzobebah and of the clans of Aharhel son of Harum.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Jabez was more honorable than his brothers. His mother had named him Jabez, saying, “I gave birth to him in pain.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Jabez cried out to the God of Israel, “Oh, that you would bless me and enlarge my territory! Let your hand be with me, and keep me from harm so that I will be free from pain.” And God granted his request.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Kelub, Shuhah’s brother, was the father of Mehir, who was the father of Eshton.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Eshton was the father of Beth Rapha, Paseah and Tehinnah the father of Ir Nahash. These were the men of Rekah.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The sons of Kenaz:Othniel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10399F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10399F\"></sup> and Seraiah.The sons of Othniel:Hathath and Meonothai.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Meonothai was the father of Ophrah.Seraiah was the father of Joab,the father of Ge Harashim. It was called this because its people were skilled workers.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The sons of Caleb son of Jephunneh:Iru, Elah and Naam.The son of Elah:Kenaz.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The sons of Jehallelel:Ziph, Ziphah, Tiria and Asarel.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The sons of Ezrah:Jether, Mered, Epher and Jalon. One of Mered’s wives gave birth to Miriam,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10403G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10403G\"></sup> Shammai and Ishbah the father of Eshtemoa.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>(His wife from the tribe of Judah gave birth to Jered the father of Gedor, Heber the father of Soko, and Jekuthiel the father of Zanoah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10404H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10404H\"></sup>) These were the children of Pharaoh’s daughter Bithiah, whom Mered had married.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The sons of Hodiah’s wife, the sister of Naham:the father of Keilah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10405I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10405I\"></sup> the Garmite, and Eshtemoa the Maakathite.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10405J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10405J\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The sons of Shimon:Amnon, Rinnah, Ben-Hanan and Tilon.The descendants of Ishi:Zoheth and Ben-Zoheth.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The sons of Shelah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10407K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10407K\"></sup> son of Judah:Er the father of Lekah, Laadah the father of Mareshah and the clans of the linen workers at Beth Ashbea,",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Jokim, the men of Kozeba, and Joash and Saraph, who ruled in Moab and Jashubi Lehem. (These records are from ancient times.)",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>They were the potters who lived at Netaim and Gederah; they stayed there and worked for the king.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The descendants of Simeon:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10410M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10410M\"></sup>Nemuel, Jamin, Jarib,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10410N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10410N\"></sup> Zerah and Shaul;",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Shallum was Shaul’s son, Mibsam his son and Mishma his son.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The descendants of Mishma:Hammuel his son, Zakkur his son and Shimei his son.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Shimei had sixteen sons and six daughters, but his brothers did not have many children; so their entire clan did not become as numerous as the people of Judah.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>They lived in Beersheba,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10414O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10414O\"></sup> Moladah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10414P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10414P\"></sup> Hazar Shual,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Bilhah, Ezem,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10415Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10415Q\"></sup> Tolad,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Bethuel, Hormah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10416R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10416R\"></sup> Ziklag,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10416S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10416S\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Beth Markaboth, Hazar Susim, Beth Biri and Shaaraim.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10417T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10417T\"></sup> These were their towns until the reign of David.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Their surrounding villages were Etam, Ain,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10418U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10418U\"></sup> Rimmon, Token and Ashan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10418V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10418V\"></sup>—five towns—",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>and all the villages around these towns as far as Baalath. These were their settlements. And they kept a genealogical record.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Meshobab, Jamlech, Joshah son of Amaziah,",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Joel, Jehu son of Joshibiah, the son of Seraiah, the son of Asiel,",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>also Elioenai, Jaakobah, Jeshohaiah, Asaiah, Adiel, Jesimiel, Benaiah,",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>and Ziza son of Shiphi, the son of Allon, the son of Jedaiah, the son of Shimri, the son of Shemaiah.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>The men listed above by name were leaders of their clans. Their families increased greatly,",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>and they went to the outskirts of Gedor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10425W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10425W\"></sup> to the east of the valley in search of pasture for their flocks.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>They found rich, good pasture, and the land was spacious, peaceful and quiet.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10426X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10426X\"></sup> Some Hamites had lived there formerly.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>The men whose names were listed came in the days of Hezekiah king of Judah. They attacked the Hamites in their dwellings and also the Meunites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10427Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10427Y\"></sup> who were there and completely destroyed them, as is evident to this day. Then they settled in their place, because there was pasture for their flocks.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>And five hundred of these Simeonites, led by Pelatiah, Neariah, Rephaiah and Uzziel, the sons of Ishi, invaded the hill country of Seir.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10428Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10428Z\"></sup>",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>They killed the remaining Amalekites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10429AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10429AA\"></sup> who had escaped, and they have lived there to this day."
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span>The sons of Reuben<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10430A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10430A\"></sup> the firstborn of Israel (he was the firstborn, but when he defiled his father’s marriage bed,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10430B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10430B\"></sup> his rights as firstborn were given to the sons of Joseph<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10430C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10430C\"></sup> son of Israel;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10430D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10430D\"></sup> so he could not be listed in the genealogical record in accordance with his birthright,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10430E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10430E\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and though Judah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10431F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10431F\"></sup> was the strongest of his brothers and a ruler<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10431G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10431G\"></sup> came from him, the rights of the firstborn<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10431H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10431H\"></sup> belonged to Joseph)—",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>the sons of Reuben<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10432I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10432I\"></sup> the firstborn of Israel:Hanok, Pallu,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10432J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10432J\"></sup> Hezron<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10432K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10432K\"></sup> and Karmi.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The descendants of Joel:Shemaiah his son, Gog his son,Shimei his son,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Micah his son,Reaiah his son, Baal his son,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>and Beerah his son, whom Tiglath-Pileser<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10435L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10435L\"></sup> king of Assyria took into exile. Beerah was a leader of the Reubenites.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Their relatives by clans,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10436M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10436M\"></sup> listed according to their genealogical records:Jeiel the chief, Zechariah,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>and Bela son of Azaz, the son of Shema, the son of Joel. They settled in the area from Aroer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10437N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10437N\"></sup> to Nebo<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10437O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10437O\"></sup> and Baal Meon.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10437P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10437P\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>To the east they occupied the land up to the edge of the desert that extends to the Euphrates<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10438Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10438Q\"></sup> River, because their livestock had increased in Gilead.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10438R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10438R\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>During Saul’s reign they waged war against the Hagrites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10439S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10439S\"></sup>, who were defeated at their hands; they occupied the dwellings of the Hagrites throughout the entire region east of Gilead.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The Gadites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10440T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10440T\"></sup> lived next to them in Bashan, as far as Salekah:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10440U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10440U\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Joel was the chief, Shapham the second, then Janai and Shaphat, in Bashan.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Their relatives, by families, were:Michael, Meshullam, Sheba, Jorai, Jakan, Zia and Eber—seven in all.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>These were the sons of Abihail son of Huri, the son of Jaroah, the son of Gilead, the son of Michael, the son of Jeshishai, the son of Jahdo, the son of Buz.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Ahi son of Abdiel, the son of Guni, was head of their family.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The Gadites lived in Gilead, in Bashan and its outlying villages, and on all the pasturelands of Sharon as far as they extended.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>All these were entered in the genealogical records during the reigns of Jotham<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10446V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10446V\"></sup> king of Judah and Jeroboam<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10446W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10446W\"></sup> king of Israel.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The Reubenites, the Gadites and the half-tribe of Manasseh had 44,760 men ready for military service<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10447X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10447X\"></sup>—able-bodied men who could handle shield and sword, who could use a bow, and who were trained for battle.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>They waged war against the Hagrites, Jetur,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10448Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10448Y\"></sup> Naphish and Nodab.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>They were helped<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10449Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10449Z\"></sup> in fighting them, and God delivered the Hagrites and all their allies into their hands, because they cried<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10449AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10449AA\"></sup> out to him during the battle. He answered their prayers, because they trusted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10449AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10449AB\"></sup> in him.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>They seized the livestock of the Hagrites—fifty thousand camels, two hundred fifty thousand sheep and two thousand donkeys. They also took one hundred thousand people captive,",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>and many others fell slain, because the battle<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10451AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10451AC\"></sup> was God’s. And they occupied the land until the exile.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10451AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10451AD\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The people of the half-tribe of Manasseh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10452AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10452AE\"></sup> were numerous; they settled in the land from Bashan to Baal Hermon, that is, to Senir (Mount Hermon).<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10452AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10452AF\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>These were the heads of their families: Epher, Ishi, Eliel, Azriel, Jeremiah, Hodaviah and Jahdiel. They were brave warriors, famous men, and heads of their families.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>But they were unfaithful<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10454AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10454AG\"></sup> to the God of their ancestors and prostituted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10454AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10454AH\"></sup> themselves to the gods of the peoples of the land, whom God had destroyed before them.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>So the God of Israel stirred up the spirit<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10455AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10455AI\"></sup> of Pul<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10455AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10455AJ\"></sup> king of Assyria (that is, Tiglath-Pileser<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10455AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10455AK\"></sup> king of Assyria), who took the Reubenites, the Gadites and the half-tribe of Manasseh into exile. He took them to Halah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10455AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10455AL\"></sup> Habor, Hara and the river of Gozan, where they are to this day."
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span>The sons of Levi:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10456A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10456A\"></sup>Gershon, Kohath and Merari.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The sons of Kohath:Amram, Izhar, Hebron and Uzziel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10457B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10457B\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The children of Amram:Aaron, Moses and Miriam.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10458C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10458C\"></sup>The sons of Aaron:Nadab, Abihu,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10458D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10458D\"></sup> Eleazar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10458E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10458E\"></sup> and Ithamar.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10458F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10458F\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Eleazar was the father of Phinehas,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10459G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10459G\"></sup>Phinehas the father of Abishua,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Abishua the father of Bukki,Bukki the father of Uzzi,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Uzzi the father of Zerahiah,Zerahiah the father of Meraioth,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Meraioth the father of Amariah,Amariah the father of Ahitub,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Ahitub the father of Zadok,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10463H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10463H\"></sup>Zadok the father of Ahimaaz,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Ahimaaz the father of Azariah,Azariah the father of Johanan,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Johanan the father of Azariah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10465I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10465I\"></sup> (it was he who served as priest in the temple Solomon built in Jerusalem),",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Azariah the father of Amariah,Amariah the father of Ahitub,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Ahitub the father of Zadok,Zadok the father of Shallum,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Shallum the father of Hilkiah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10468J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10468J\"></sup>Hilkiah the father of Azariah,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Azariah the father of Seraiah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10469K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10469K\"></sup>and Seraiah the father of Jozadak.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Jozadak<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10470L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10470L\"></sup> was deported when the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sent Judah and Jerusalem into exile by the hand of Nebuchadnezzar.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The sons of Levi:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10471M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10471M\"></sup>Gershon, Kohath and Merari.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10471N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10471N\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>These are the names of the sons of Gershon:Libni and Shimei.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10472O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10472O\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The sons of Kohath:Amram, Izhar, Hebron and Uzziel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10473P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10473P\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The sons of Merari:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10474Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10474Q\"></sup>Mahli and Mushi.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10474R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10474R\"></sup>These are the clans of the Levites listed according to their fathers:",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Of Gershon:Libni his son, Jahath his son,Zimmah his son,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Joah his son,Iddo his son, Zerah his sonand Jeatherai his son.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The descendants of Kohath:Amminadab his son, Korah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10477S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10477S\"></sup> his son,Assir his son,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Elkanah his son,Ebiasaph his son, Assir his son,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Tahath his son, Uriel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10479T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10479T\"></sup> his son,Uzziah his son and Shaul his son.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>The descendants of Elkanah:Amasai, Ahimoth,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Elkanah his son, Zophai his son,Nahath his son,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Eliab his son,Jeroham his son, Elkanah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10482U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10482U\"></sup> his sonand Samuel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10482V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10482V\"></sup> his son.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>The sons of Samuel:Joel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10483W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10483W\"></sup> the firstbornand Abijah the second son.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>The descendants of Merari:Mahli, Libni his son,Shimei his son, Uzzah his son,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Shimea his son, Haggiah his sonand Asaiah his son.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>These are the men<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10486Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10486Y\"></sup> David put in charge of the music<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10486Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10486Z\"></sup> in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> after the ark came to rest there.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>They ministered with music before the tabernacle, the tent of meeting, until Solomon built the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in Jerusalem. They performed their duties according to the regulations laid down for them.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Here are the men who served, together with their sons:From the Kohathites:Heman,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10488AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10488AA\"></sup> the musician,the son of Joel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10488AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10488AB\"></sup> the son of Samuel,",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>the son of Elkanah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10489AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10489AC\"></sup> the son of Jeroham,the son of Eliel, the son of Toah,",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>the son of Zuph, the son of Elkanah,the son of Mahath, the son of Amasai,",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>the son of Elkanah, the son of Joel,the son of Azariah, the son of Zephaniah,",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>the son of Tahath, the son of Assir,the son of Ebiasaph, the son of Korah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10492AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10492AD\"></sup>",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>the son of Izhar,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10493AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10493AE\"></sup> the son of Kohath,the son of Levi, the son of Israel;",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>and Heman’s associate Asaph,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10494AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10494AF\"></sup> who served at his right hand:Asaph son of Berekiah, the son of Shimea,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10494AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10494AG\"></sup>",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>the son of Michael, the son of Baaseiah,the son of Malkijah,",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>the son of Ethni,the son of Zerah, the son of Adaiah,",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>the son of Ethan, the son of Zimmah,the son of Shimei,",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>the son of Jahath,the son of Gershon, the son of Levi;",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>and from their associates, the Merarites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10499AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10499AH\"></sup> at his left hand:Ethan son of Kishi, the son of Abdi,the son of Malluk,",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>the son of Hashabiah,the son of Amaziah, the son of Hilkiah,",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>the son of Amzi, the son of Bani,the son of Shemer,",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>the son of Mahli,the son of Mushi, the son of Merari,the son of Levi.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>Their fellow Levites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10503AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10503AI\"></sup> were assigned to all the other duties of the tabernacle, the house of God.",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>But Aaron and his descendants were the ones who presented offerings on the altar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10504AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10504AJ\"></sup> of burnt offering and on the altar of incense<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10504AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10504AK\"></sup> in connection with all that was done in the Most Holy Place, making atonement for Israel, in accordance with all that Moses the servant of God had commanded.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>These were the descendants of Aaron:Eleazar his son, Phinehas his son,Abishua his son,",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>Bukki his son,Uzzi his son, Zerahiah his son,",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>Meraioth his son, Amariah his son,Ahitub his son,",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>Zadok<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10508AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10508AL\"></sup> his sonand Ahimaaz his son.",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>These were the locations of their settlements<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10509AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10509AM\"></sup> allotted as their territory (they were assigned to the descendants of Aaron who were from the Kohathite clan, because the first lot was for them):",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>They were given Hebron in Judah with its surrounding pasturelands.",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>But the fields and villages around the city were given to Caleb son of Jephunneh.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10511AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10511AN\"></sup>",
			"57": "<sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup>So the descendants of Aaron were given Hebron (a city of refuge), and Libnah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10512AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10512AO\"></sup> Jattir,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10512AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10512AP\"></sup> Eshtemoa,",
			"58": "<sup class=\"versenum\">58 </sup>Hilen, Debir,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10513AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10513AQ\"></sup>",
			"59": "<sup class=\"versenum\">59 </sup>Ashan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10514AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10514AR\"></sup> Juttah and Beth Shemesh, together with their pasturelands.",
			"60": "<sup class=\"versenum\">60 </sup>And from the tribe of Benjamin they were given Gibeon, Geba, Alemeth and Anathoth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10515AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10515AS\"></sup> together with their pasturelands.The total number of towns distributed among the Kohathite clans came to thirteen.",
			"61": "<sup class=\"versenum\">61 </sup>The rest of Kohath’s descendants were allotted ten towns from the clans of half the tribe of Manasseh.",
			"62": "<sup class=\"versenum\">62 </sup>The descendants of Gershon, clan by clan, were allotted thirteen towns from the tribes of Issachar, Asher and Naphtali, and from the part of the tribe of Manasseh that is in Bashan.",
			"63": "<sup class=\"versenum\">63 </sup>The descendants of Merari, clan by clan, were allotted twelve towns from the tribes of Reuben, Gad and Zebulun.",
			"64": "<sup class=\"versenum\">64 </sup>So the Israelites gave the Levites these towns<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10519AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10519AT\"></sup> and their pasturelands.",
			"65": "<sup class=\"versenum\">65 </sup>From the tribes of Judah, Simeon and Benjamin they allotted the previously named towns.",
			"66": "<sup class=\"versenum\">66 </sup>Some of the Kohathite clans were given as their territory towns from the tribe of Ephraim.",
			"67": "<sup class=\"versenum\">67 </sup>In the hill country of Ephraim they were given Shechem (a city of refuge), and Gezer,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10522AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10522AU\"></sup>",
			"68": "<sup class=\"versenum\">68 </sup>Jokmeam,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10523AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10523AV\"></sup> Beth Horon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10523AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10523AW\"></sup>",
			"69": "<sup class=\"versenum\">69 </sup>Aijalon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10524AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10524AX\"></sup> and Gath Rimmon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10524AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10524AY\"></sup> together with their pasturelands.",
			"70": "<sup class=\"versenum\">70 </sup>And from half the tribe of Manasseh the Israelites gave Aner and Bileam, together with their pasturelands, to the rest of the Kohathite clans.",
			"71": "<sup class=\"versenum\">71 </sup>The Gershonites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10526AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10526AZ\"></sup> received the following:From the clan of the half-tribe of Manassehthey received Golan in Bashan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10526BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10526BA\"></sup> and also Ashtaroth, together with their pasturelands;",
			"72": "<sup class=\"versenum\">72 </sup>from the tribe of Issacharthey received Kedesh, Daberath,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10527BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10527BB\"></sup>",
			"73": "<sup class=\"versenum\">73 </sup>Ramoth and Anem, together with their pasturelands;",
			"74": "<sup class=\"versenum\">74 </sup>from the tribe of Asherthey received Mashal, Abdon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10529BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10529BC\"></sup>",
			"75": "<sup class=\"versenum\">75 </sup>Hukok<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10530BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10530BD\"></sup> and Rehob,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10530BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10530BE\"></sup> together with their pasturelands;",
			"76": "<sup class=\"versenum\">76 </sup>and from the tribe of Naphtalithey received Kedesh in Galilee, Hammon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10531BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10531BF\"></sup> and Kiriathaim,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10531BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10531BG\"></sup> together with their pasturelands.",
			"77": "<sup class=\"versenum\">77 </sup>The Merarites (the rest of the Levites) received the following:From the tribe of Zebulunthey received Jokneam, Kartah, Rimmono and Tabor, together with their pasturelands;",
			"78": "<sup class=\"versenum\">78 </sup>from the tribe of Reuben across the Jordan east of Jerichothey received Bezer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10533BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10533BH\"></sup> in the wilderness, Jahzah,",
			"79": "<sup class=\"versenum\">79 </sup>Kedemoth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10534BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10534BI\"></sup> and Mephaath, together with their pasturelands;",
			"80": "<sup class=\"versenum\">80 </sup>and from the tribe of Gadthey received Ramoth in Gilead,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10535BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10535BJ\"></sup> Mahanaim,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10535BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10535BK\"></sup>",
			"81": "<sup class=\"versenum\">81 </sup>Heshbon and Jazer,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10536BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10536BL\"></sup> together with their pasturelands.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10536BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10536BM\"></sup>"
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span>The sons of Issachar:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10537A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10537A\"></sup>Tola, Puah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10537B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10537B\"></sup> Jashub and Shimron—four in all.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The sons of Tola:Uzzi, Rephaiah, Jeriel, Jahmai, Ibsam and Samuel—heads of their families. During the reign of David, the descendants of Tola listed as fighting men in their genealogy numbered 22,600.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The son of Uzzi:Izrahiah.The sons of Izrahiah:Michael, Obadiah, Joel and Ishiah. All five of them were chiefs.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>According to their family genealogy, they had 36,000 men ready for battle, for they had many wives and children.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The relatives who were fighting men belonging to all the clans of Issachar, as listed in their genealogy, were 87,000 in all.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Three sons of Benjamin:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10542C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10542C\"></sup>Bela, Beker and Jediael.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The sons of Bela:Ezbon, Uzzi, Uzziel, Jerimoth and Iri, heads of families—five in all. Their genealogical record listed 22,034 fighting men.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The sons of Beker:Zemirah, Joash, Eliezer, Elioenai, Omri, Jeremoth, Abijah, Anathoth and Alemeth. All these were the sons of Beker.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Their genealogical record listed the heads of families and 20,200 fighting men.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The son of Jediael:Bilhan.The sons of Bilhan:Jeush, Benjamin, Ehud, Kenaanah, Zethan, Tarshish and Ahishahar.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>All these sons of Jediael were heads of families. There were 17,200 fighting men ready to go out to war.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The Shuppites and Huppites were the descendants of Ir, and the Hushites the descendants of Aher.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The sons of Naphtali:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10549D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10549D\"></sup>Jahziel, Guni, Jezer and Shillem—the descendants of Bilhah.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The descendants of Manasseh:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10550E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10550E\"></sup>Asriel was his descendant through his Aramean concubine. She gave birth to Makir the father of Gilead.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10550F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10550F\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Makir took a wife from among the Huppites and Shuppites. His sister’s name was Maakah.Another descendant was named Zelophehad,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10551G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10551G\"></sup> who had only daughters.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Makir’s wife Maakah gave birth to a son and named him Peresh. His brother was named Sheresh, and his sons were Ulam and Rakem.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The son of Ulam:Bedan.These were the sons of Gilead<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10553H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10553H\"></sup> son of Makir, the son of Manasseh.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>His sister Hammoleketh gave birth to Ishhod, Abiezer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10554I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10554I\"></sup> and Mahlah.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The sons of Shemida<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10555J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10555J\"></sup> were:Ahian, Shechem, Likhi and Aniam.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The descendants of Ephraim:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10556K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10556K\"></sup>Shuthelah, Bered his son,Tahath his son, Eleadah his son,Tahath his son,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Zabad his sonand Shuthelah his son.Ezer and Elead were killed by the native-born men of Gath, when they went down to seize their livestock.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Their father Ephraim mourned for them many days, and his relatives came to comfort him.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then he made love to his wife again, and she became pregnant and gave birth to a son. He named him Beriah, because there had been misfortune in his family.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>His daughter was Sheerah, who built Lower and Upper Beth Horon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10560L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10560L\"></sup> as well as Uzzen Sheerah.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Rephah was his son, Resheph his son,Telah his son, Tahan his son,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Ladan his son, Ammihud his son,Elishama his son,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Nun his sonand Joshua his son.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Their lands and settlements included Bethel and its surrounding villages, Naaran to the east, Gezer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10564M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10564M\"></sup> and its villages to the west, and Shechem and its villages all the way to Ayyah and its villages.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Along the borders of Manasseh were Beth Shan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10565N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10565N\"></sup> Taanach, Megiddo and Dor,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10565O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10565O\"></sup> together with their villages. The descendants of Joseph son of Israel lived in these towns.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>The sons of Asher:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10566P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10566P\"></sup>Imnah, Ishvah, Ishvi and Beriah. Their sister was Serah.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>The sons of Beriah:Heber and Malkiel, who was the father of Birzaith.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Heber was the father of Japhlet, Shomer and Hotham and of their sister Shua.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>The sons of Japhlet:Pasak, Bimhal and Ashvath.These were Japhlet’s sons.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>The sons of Shomer:Ahi, Rohgah, Hubbah and Aram.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>The sons of his brother Helem:Zophah, Imna, Shelesh and Amal.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>The sons of Zophah:Suah, Harnepher, Shual, Beri, Imrah,",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Bezer, Hod, Shamma, Shilshah, Ithran and Beera.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>The sons of Jether:Jephunneh, Pispah and Ara.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>The sons of Ulla:Arah, Hanniel and Rizia.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>All these were descendants of Asher—heads of families, choice men, brave warriors and outstanding leaders. The number of men ready for battle, as listed in their genealogy, was 26,000."
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span>Benjamin<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10577B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10577B\"></sup> was the father of Bela his firstborn,Ashbel the second son, Aharah the third,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Nohah the fourth and Rapha the fifth.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The sons of Bela were:Addar,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10579C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10579C\"></sup> Gera, Abihud,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Abishua, Naaman, Ahoah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10580D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10580D\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Gera, Shephuphan and Huram.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>These were the descendants of Ehud,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10582E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10582E\"></sup> who were heads of families of those living in Geba and were deported to Manahath:",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Naaman, Ahijah, and Gera, who deported them and who was the father of Uzza and Ahihud.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Sons were born to Shaharaim in Moab after he had divorced his wives Hushim and Baara.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>By his wife Hodesh he had Jobab, Zibia, Mesha, Malkam,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Jeuz, Sakia and Mirmah. These were his sons, heads of families.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>By Hushim he had Abitub and Elpaal.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The sons of Elpaal:Eber, Misham, Shemed (who built Ono<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10588F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10588F\"></sup> and Lod with its surrounding villages),",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and Beriah and Shema, who were heads of families of those living in Aijalon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10589G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10589G\"></sup> and who drove out the inhabitants of Gath.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10589H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10589H\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Ahio, Shashak, Jeremoth,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Zebadiah, Arad, Eder,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Michael, Ishpah and Joha were the sons of Beriah.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Zebadiah, Meshullam, Hizki, Heber,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Ishmerai, Izliah and Jobab were the sons of Elpaal.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Jakim, Zikri, Zabdi,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Elienai, Zillethai, Eliel,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Adaiah, Beraiah and Shimrath were the sons of Shimei.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Ishpan, Eber, Eliel,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Abdon, Zikri, Hanan,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Hananiah, Elam, Anthothijah,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Iphdeiah and Penuel were the sons of Shashak.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Shamsherai, Shehariah, Athaliah,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Jaareshiah, Elijah and Zikri were the sons of Jeroham.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>All these were heads of families, chiefs as listed in their genealogy, and they lived in Jerusalem.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Jeiel the father of Gibeon lived in Gibeon.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10605I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10605I\"></sup>His wife’s name was Maakah,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>and his firstborn son was Abdon, followed by Zur, Kish, Baal, Ner, Nadab,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Gedor, Ahio, Zeker",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>and Mikloth, who was the father of Shimeah. They too lived near their relatives in Jerusalem.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Ner<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10609J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10609J\"></sup> was the father of Kish,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10609K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10609K\"></sup> Kish the father of Saul<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10609L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10609L\"></sup>, and Saul the father of Jonathan, Malki-Shua, Abinadab and Esh-Baal.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10609M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10609M\"></sup>",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>The son of Jonathan:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10610N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10610N\"></sup>Merib-Baal,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10610O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10610O\"></sup> who was the father of Micah.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>The sons of Micah:Pithon, Melek, Tarea and Ahaz.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Ahaz was the father of Jehoaddah, Jehoaddah was the father of Alemeth, Azmaveth and Zimri, and Zimri was the father of Moza.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Moza was the father of Binea; Raphah was his son, Eleasah his son and Azel his son.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Azel had six sons, and these were their names:Azrikam, Bokeru, Ishmael, Sheariah, Obadiah and Hanan. All these were the sons of Azel.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>The sons of his brother Eshek:Ulam his firstborn, Jeush the second son and Eliphelet the third.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>The sons of Ulam were brave warriors who could handle the bow. They had many sons and grandsons—150 in all.All these were the descendants of Benjamin.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10616P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10616P\"></sup>"
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span>All Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10617A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10617A\"></sup> was listed in the genealogies recorded in the book of the kings of Israel and Judah. They were taken captive to Babylon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10617B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10617B\"></sup> because of their unfaithfulness.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10617C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10617C\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Now the first to resettle on their own property in their own towns<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10618E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10618E\"></sup> were some Israelites, priests, Levites and temple servants.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10618F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10618F\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Those from Judah, from Benjamin, and from Ephraim and Manasseh who lived in Jerusalem were:",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Uthai son of Ammihud, the son of Omri, the son of Imri, the son of Bani, a descendant of Perez son of Judah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10620G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10620G\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Of the Shelanites:Asaiah the firstborn and his sons.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Of the Zerahites:Jeuel.The people from Judah numbered 690.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Of the Benjamites:Sallu son of Meshullam, the son of Hodaviah, the son of Hassenuah;",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Ibneiah son of Jeroham; Elah son of Uzzi, the son of Mikri; and Meshullam son of Shephatiah, the son of Reuel, the son of Ibnijah.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The people from Benjamin, as listed in their genealogy, numbered 956. All these men were heads of their families.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Of the priests:Jedaiah; Jehoiarib; Jakin;",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Azariah son of Hilkiah, the son of Meshullam, the son of Zadok, the son of Meraioth, the son of Ahitub, the official in charge of the house of God;",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Adaiah son of Jeroham, the son of Pashhur,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10628H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10628H\"></sup> the son of Malkijah; and Maasai son of Adiel, the son of Jahzerah, the son of Meshullam, the son of Meshillemith, the son of Immer.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The priests, who were heads of families, numbered 1,760. They were able men, responsible for ministering in the house of God.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Of the Levites:Shemaiah son of Hasshub, the son of Azrikam, the son of Hashabiah, a Merarite;",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Bakbakkar, Heresh, Galal and Mattaniah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10631I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10631I\"></sup> son of Mika, the son of Zikri, the son of Asaph;",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Obadiah son of Shemaiah, the son of Galal, the son of Jeduthun; and Berekiah son of Asa, the son of Elkanah, who lived in the villages of the Netophathites.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10632J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10632J\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The gatekeepers:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10633K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10633K\"></sup>Shallum, Akkub, Talmon, Ahiman and their fellow Levites, Shallum their chief",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>being stationed at the King’s Gate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10634L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10634L\"></sup> on the east, up to the present time. These were the gatekeepers belonging to the camp of the Levites.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Shallum<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10635M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10635M\"></sup> son of Kore, the son of Ebiasaph, the son of Korah, and his fellow gatekeepers from his family (the Korahites) were responsible for guarding the thresholds of the tent just as their ancestors had been responsible for guarding the entrance to the dwelling of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>In earlier times Phinehas<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10636N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10636N\"></sup> son of Eleazar was the official in charge of the gatekeepers, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was with him.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Zechariah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10637O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10637O\"></sup> son of Meshelemiah was the gatekeeper at the entrance to the tent of meeting.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Altogether, those chosen to be gatekeepers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10638P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10638P\"></sup> at the thresholds numbered 212. They were registered by genealogy in their villages. The gatekeepers had been assigned to their positions of trust by David and Samuel the seer.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10638Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10638Q\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>They and their descendants were in charge of guarding the gates of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>—the house called the tent of meeting.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The gatekeepers were on the four sides: east, west, north and south.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Their fellow Levites in their villages had to come from time to time and share their duties for seven-day<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10641R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10641R\"></sup> periods.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>But the four principal gatekeepers, who were Levites, were entrusted with the responsibility for the rooms and treasuries<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10642S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10642S\"></sup> in the house of God.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>They would spend the night stationed around the house of God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10643T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10643T\"></sup> because they had to guard it; and they had charge of the key<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10643U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10643U\"></sup> for opening it each morning.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Some of them were in charge of the articles used in the temple service; they counted them when they were brought in and when they were taken out.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Others were assigned to take care of the furnishings and all the other articles of the sanctuary,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10645V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10645V\"></sup> as well as the special flour and wine, and the olive oil, incense and spices.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>But some<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10646W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10646W\"></sup> of the priests took care of mixing the spices.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>A Levite named Mattithiah, the firstborn son of Shallum the Korahite, was entrusted with the responsibility for baking the offering bread.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Some of the Kohathites, their fellow Levites, were in charge of preparing for every Sabbath the bread set out on the table.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10648X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10648X\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Those who were musicians,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10649Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10649Y\"></sup> heads of Levite families, stayed in the rooms of the temple and were exempt from other duties because they were responsible for the work day and night.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10649Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10649Z\"></sup>",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>All these were heads of Levite families, chiefs as listed in their genealogy, and they lived in Jerusalem.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Jeiel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10651AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10651AB\"></sup> the father of Gibeon lived in Gibeon.His wife’s name was Maakah,",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>and his firstborn son was Abdon, followed by Zur, Kish, Baal, Ner, Nadab,",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Gedor, Ahio, Zechariah and Mikloth.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Mikloth was the father of Shimeam. They too lived near their relatives in Jerusalem.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Ner<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10655AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10655AC\"></sup> was the father of Kish,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10655AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10655AD\"></sup> Kish the father of Saul, and Saul the father of Jonathan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10655AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10655AE\"></sup> Malki-Shua, Abinadab and Esh-Baal.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10655AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10655AF\"></sup>",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>The son of Jonathan:Merib-Baal,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10656AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10656AG\"></sup> who was the father of Micah.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>The sons of Micah:Pithon, Melek, Tahrea and Ahaz.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Ahaz was the father of Jadah, Jadah was the father of Alemeth, Azmaveth and Zimri, and Zimri was the father of Moza.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Moza was the father of Binea; Rephaiah was his son, Eleasah his son and Azel his son.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Azel had six sons, and these were their names:Azrikam, Bokeru, Ishmael, Sheariah, Obadiah and Hanan. These were the sons of Azel."
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span>Now the Philistines fought against Israel; the Israelites fled before them, and many fell dead on Mount Gilboa.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The Philistines were in hot pursuit of Saul and his sons, and they killed his sons Jonathan, Abinadab and Malki-Shua.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The fighting grew fierce around Saul, and when the archers overtook him, they wounded him.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Saul said to his armor-bearer, “Draw your sword and run me through, or these uncircumcised fellows will come and abuse me.”But his armor-bearer was terrified and would not do it; so Saul took his own sword and fell on it.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When the armor-bearer saw that Saul was dead, he too fell on his sword and died.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So Saul and his three sons died, and all his house died together.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When all the Israelites in the valley saw that the army had fled and that Saul and his sons had died, they abandoned their towns and fled. And the Philistines came and occupied them.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The next day, when the Philistines came to strip the dead, they found Saul and his sons fallen on Mount Gilboa.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>They stripped him and took his head and his armor, and sent messengers throughout the land of the Philistines to proclaim the news among their idols and their people.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>They put his armor in the temple of their gods and hung up his head in the temple of Dagon.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10670B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10670B\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>When all the inhabitants of Jabesh Gilead<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10671C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10671C\"></sup> heard what the Philistines had done to Saul,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>all their valiant men went and took the bodies of Saul and his sons and brought them to Jabesh. Then they buried their bones under the great tree in Jabesh, and they fasted seven days.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Saul died<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10673D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10673D\"></sup> because he was unfaithful<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10673E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10673E\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; he did not keep<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10673F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10673F\"></sup> the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and even consulted a medium<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10673G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10673G\"></sup> for guidance,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and did not inquire of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> put him to death and turned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10674H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10674H\"></sup> the kingdom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10674I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10674I\"></sup> over to David son of Jesse."
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">11 </span>All Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10675B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10675B\"></sup> came together to David at Hebron<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10675C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10675C\"></sup> and said, “We are your own flesh and blood.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>In the past, even while Saul was king, you were the one who led Israel on their military campaigns.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10676D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10676D\"></sup> And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God said to you, ‘You will shepherd<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10676E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10676E\"></sup> my people Israel, and you will become their ruler.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10676F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10676F\"></sup>’”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>When all the elders of Israel had come to King David at Hebron, he made a covenant with them at Hebron before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and they anointed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10677G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10677G\"></sup> David king over Israel, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had promised through Samuel.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>David and all the Israelites marched to Jerusalem (that is, Jebus). The Jebusites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10678I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10678I\"></sup> who lived there",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>said to David, “You will not get in here.” Nevertheless, David captured the fortress of Zion—which is the City of David.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>David had said, “Whoever leads the attack on the Jebusites will become commander-in-chief.” Joab<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10680J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10680J\"></sup> son of Zeruiah went up first, and so he received the command.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>David then took up residence in the fortress, and so it was called the City of David.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He built up the city around it, from the terraces<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10682K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10682K\"></sup> to the surrounding wall, while Joab restored the rest of the city.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And David became more and more powerful,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10683L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10683L\"></sup> because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> Almighty was with him.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>These were the chiefs of David’s mighty warriors—they, together with all Israel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10684N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10684N\"></sup> gave his kingship strong support to extend it over the whole land, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had promised<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10684O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10684O\"></sup>—",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>this is the list of David’s mighty warriors:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10685P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10685P\"></sup>Jashobeam, a Hakmonite, was chief of the officers; he raised his spear against three hundred men, whom he killed in one encounter.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Next to him was Eleazar son of Dodai the Ahohite, one of the three mighty warriors.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>He was with David at Pas Dammim when the Philistines gathered there for battle. At a place where there was a field full of barley, the troops fled from the Philistines.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But they took their stand in the middle of the field. They defended it and struck the Philistines down, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> brought about a great victory.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10688Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10688Q\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Three of the thirty chiefs came down to David to the rock at the cave of Adullam, while a band of Philistines was encamped in the Valley<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10689R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10689R\"></sup> of Rephaim.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>At that time David was in the stronghold,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10690S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10690S\"></sup> and the Philistine garrison was at Bethlehem.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>David longed for water and said, “Oh, that someone would get me a drink of water from the well near the gate of Bethlehem!”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>So the Three broke through the Philistine lines, drew water from the well near the gate of Bethlehem and carried it back to David. But he refused to drink it; instead, he poured<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10692T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10692T\"></sup> it out to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“God forbid that I should do this!” he said. “Should I drink the blood of these men who went at the risk of their lives?” Because they risked their lives to bring it back, David would not drink it.Such were the exploits of the three mighty warriors.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Abishai<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10694U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10694U\"></sup> the brother of Joab was chief of the Three. He raised his spear against three hundred men, whom he killed, and so he became as famous as the Three.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>He was doubly honored above the Three and became their commander, even though he was not included among them.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Benaiah son of Jehoiada, a valiant fighter from Kabzeel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10696V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10696V\"></sup> performed great exploits. He struck down Moab’s two mightiest warriors. He also went down into a pit on a snowy day and killed a lion.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10696W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10696W\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And he struck down an Egyptian who was five cubits tall. Although the Egyptian had a spear like a weaver’s rod<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10697X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10697X\"></sup> in his hand, Benaiah went against him with a club. He snatched the spear from the Egyptian’s hand and killed him with his own spear.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Such were the exploits of Benaiah son of Jehoiada; he too was as famous as the three mighty warriors.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>He was held in greater honor than any of the Thirty, but he was not included among the Three. And David put him in charge of his bodyguard.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The mighty warriors were:Asahel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10700Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10700Y\"></sup> the brother of Joab,Elhanan son of Dodo from Bethlehem,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Shammoth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10701Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10701Z\"></sup> the Harorite,Helez the Pelonite,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Ira son of Ikkesh from Tekoa,Abiezer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10702AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10702AA\"></sup> from Anathoth,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Sibbekai<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10703AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10703AB\"></sup> the Hushathite,Ilai the Ahohite,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Maharai the Netophathite,Heled son of Baanah the Netophathite,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Ithai son of Ribai from Gibeah in Benjamin,Benaiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10705AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10705AC\"></sup> the Pirathonite,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10705AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10705AD\"></sup>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Hurai from the ravines of Gaash,Abiel the Arbathite,",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Azmaveth the Baharumite,Eliahba the Shaalbonite,",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>the sons of Hashem the Gizonite,Jonathan son of Shagee the Hararite,",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Ahiam son of Sakar the Hararite,Eliphal son of Ur,",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Hepher the Mekerathite,Ahijah the Pelonite,",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Hezro the Carmelite,Naarai son of Ezbai,",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Joel the brother of Nathan,Mibhar son of Hagri,",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Zelek the Ammonite,Naharai the Berothite, the armor-bearer of Joab son of Zeruiah,",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Ira the Ithrite,Gareb the Ithrite,",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Uriah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10715AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10715AE\"></sup> the Hittite,Zabad<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10715AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10715AF\"></sup> son of Ahlai,",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Adina son of Shiza the Reubenite, who was chief of the Reubenites, and the thirty with him,",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Hanan son of Maakah,Joshaphat the Mithnite,",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Uzzia the Ashterathite,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10718AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10718AG\"></sup>Shama and Jeiel the sons of Hotham the Aroerite,",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>Jediael son of Shimri,his brother Joha the Tizite,",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>Eliel the Mahavite,Jeribai and Joshaviah the sons of Elnaam,Ithmah the Moabite,",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>Eliel, Obed and Jaasiel the Mezobaite."
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">12 </span>These were the men who came to David at Ziklag,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10722A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10722A\"></sup> while he was banished from the presence of Saul son of Kish (they were among the warriors who helped him in battle;",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>they were armed with bows and were able to shoot arrows or to sling stones right-handed or left-handed;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10723B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10723B\"></sup> they were relatives of Saul<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10723C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10723C\"></sup> from the tribe of Benjamin):",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Ahiezer their chief and Joash the sons of Shemaah the Gibeathite; Jeziel and Pelet the sons of Azmaveth; Berakah, Jehu the Anathothite,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and Ishmaiah the Gibeonite, a mighty warrior among the Thirty, who was a leader of the Thirty; Jeremiah, Jahaziel, Johanan, Jozabad the Gederathite,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10725D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10725D\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Eluzai, Jerimoth, Bealiah, Shemariah and Shephatiah the Haruphite;",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Elkanah, Ishiah, Azarel, Joezer and Jashobeam the Korahites;",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and Joelah and Zebadiah the sons of Jeroham from Gedor.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10728E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10728E\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Some Gadites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10729F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10729F\"></sup> defected to David at his stronghold in the wilderness. They were brave warriors, ready for battle and able to handle the shield and spear. Their faces were the faces of lions,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10729G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10729G\"></sup> and they were as swift as gazelles<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10729H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10729H\"></sup> in the mountains.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Ezer was the chief,Obadiah the second in command, Eliab the third,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Mishmannah the fourth, Jeremiah the fifth,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Attai the sixth, Eliel the seventh,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Johanan the eighth, Elzabad the ninth,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Jeremiah the tenth and Makbannai the eleventh.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>These Gadites were army commanders; the least was a match for a hundred,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10735I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10735I\"></sup> and the greatest for a thousand.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10735J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10735J\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>It was they who crossed the Jordan in the first month when it was overflowing all its banks,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10736K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10736K\"></sup> and they put to flight everyone living in the valleys, to the east and to the west.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Other Benjamites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10737L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10737L\"></sup> and some men from Judah also came to David in his stronghold.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>David went out to meet them and said to them, “If you have come to me in peace to help me, I am ready for you to join me. But if you have come to betray me to my enemies when my hands are free from violence, may the God of our ancestors see it and judge you.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then the Spirit<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10739M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10739M\"></sup> came on Amasai,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10739N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10739N\"></sup> chief of the Thirty, and he said:“We are yours, David!We are with you, son of Jesse!Success,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10739O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10739O\"></sup> success to you,and success to those who help you,for your God will help you.”So David received them and made them leaders of his raiding bands.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Some of the tribe of Manasseh defected to David when he went with the Philistines to fight against Saul. (He and his men did not help the Philistines because, after consultation, their rulers sent him away. They said, “It will cost us our heads if he deserts to his master Saul.”)<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10740P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10740P\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>When David went to Ziklag,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10741Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10741Q\"></sup> these were the men of Manasseh who defected to him: Adnah, Jozabad, Jediael, Michael, Jozabad, Elihu and Zillethai, leaders of units of a thousand in Manasseh.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>They helped David against raiding bands, for all of them were brave warriors, and they were commanders in his army.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Day after day men came to help David, until he had a great army, like the army of God.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>These are the numbers of the men armed for battle who came to David at Hebron<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10744R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10744R\"></sup> to turn<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10744S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10744S\"></sup> Saul’s kingdom over to him, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had said:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10744T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10744T\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>from Judah, carrying shield and spear—6,800 armed for battle;",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>from Simeon, warriors ready for battle—7,100;",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>from Levi—4,600,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>including Jehoiada, leader of the family of Aaron, with 3,700 men,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>and Zadok,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10749U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10749U\"></sup> a brave young warrior, with 22 officers from his family;",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>from Benjamin,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10750V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10750V\"></sup> Saul’s tribe—3,000, most<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10750W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10750W\"></sup> of whom had remained loyal to Saul’s house until then;",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>from Ephraim, brave warriors, famous in their own clans—20,800;",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>from half the tribe of Manasseh, designated by name to come and make David king—18,000;",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>from Issachar, men who understood the times and knew what Israel should do<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10753X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10753X\"></sup>—200 chiefs, with all their relatives under their command;",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>from Zebulun, experienced soldiers prepared for battle with every type of weapon, to help David with undivided loyalty—50,000;",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>from Naphtali—1,000 officers, together with 37,000 men carrying shields and spears;",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>from Dan, ready for battle—28,600;",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>from Asher, experienced soldiers prepared for battle—40,000;",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>and from east of the Jordan, from Reuben, Gad and the half-tribe of Manasseh, armed with every type of weapon—120,000.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>All these were fighting men who volunteered to serve in the ranks. They came to Hebron fully determined to make David king over all Israel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10759Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10759Y\"></sup> All the rest of the Israelites were also of one mind to make David king.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>The men spent three days there with David, eating and drinking,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10760Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10760Z\"></sup> for their families had supplied provisions for them.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Also, their neighbors from as far away as Issachar, Zebulun and Naphtali came bringing food on donkeys, camels, mules and oxen. There were plentiful supplies<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10761AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10761AA\"></sup> of flour, fig cakes, raisin<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10761AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10761AB\"></sup> cakes, wine, olive oil, cattle and sheep, for there was joy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10761AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10761AC\"></sup> in Israel."
		},
		"13": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">13 </span>David conferred with each of his officers, the commanders of thousands and commanders of hundreds.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He then said to the whole assembly of Israel, “If it seems good to you and if it is the will of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God, let us send word far and wide to the rest of our people throughout the territories of Israel, and also to the priests and Levites who are with them in their towns and pasturelands, to come and join us.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Let us bring the ark of our God back to us,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10764B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10764B\"></sup> for we did not inquire<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10764C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10764C\"></sup> of it during the reign of Saul.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The whole assembly agreed to do this, because it seemed right to all the people.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So David assembled all Israel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10766D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10766D\"></sup> from the Shihor River<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10766E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10766E\"></sup> in Egypt to Lebo Hamath,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10766F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10766F\"></sup> to bring the ark of God from Kiriath Jearim.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10766G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10766G\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>David and all Israel went to Baalah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10767H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10767H\"></sup> of Judah (Kiriath Jearim) to bring up from there the ark of God the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, who is enthroned between the cherubim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10767I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10767I\"></sup>—the ark that is called by the Name.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>They moved the ark of God from Abinadab’s<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10768J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10768J\"></sup> house on a new cart, with Uzzah and Ahio guiding it.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>David and all the Israelites were celebrating with all their might before God, with songs and with harps, lyres, timbrels, cymbals and trumpets.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10769K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10769K\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>When they came to the threshing floor of Kidon, Uzzah reached out his hand to steady the ark, because the oxen stumbled.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s anger<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10771L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10771L\"></sup> burned against Uzzah, and he struck him down<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10771M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10771M\"></sup> because he had put his hand on the ark. So he died there before God.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then David was angry because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s wrath had broken out against Uzzah, and to this day that place is called Perez Uzzah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10772N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10772N\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>David was afraid of God that day and asked, “How can I ever bring the ark of God to me?”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>He did not take the ark to be with him in the City of David. Instead, he took it to the house of Obed-Edom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10774O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10774O\"></sup> the Gittite.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The ark of God remained with the family of Obed-Edom in his house for three months, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> blessed his household<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10775P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10775P\"></sup> and everything he had."
		},
		"14": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">14 </span>Now Hiram king of Tyre sent messengers to David, along with cedar logs,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10776B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10776B\"></sup> stonemasons and carpenters to build a palace for him.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And David knew that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had established him as king over Israel and that his kingdom had been highly exalted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10777C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10777C\"></sup> for the sake of his people Israel.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>In Jerusalem David took more wives and became the father of more sons<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10778D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10778D\"></sup> and daughters.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>These are the names of the children born to him there:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10779E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10779E\"></sup> Shammua, Shobab, Nathan, Solomon,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Ibhar, Elishua, Elpelet,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Nogah, Nepheg, Japhia,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Elishama, Beeliada and Eliphelet.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>When the Philistines heard that David had been anointed king over all Israel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10783G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10783G\"></sup> they went up in full force to search for him, but David heard about it and went out to meet them.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Now the Philistines had come and raided the Valley<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10784H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10784H\"></sup> of Rephaim;",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>so David inquired of God: “Shall I go and attack the Philistines? Will you deliver them into my hands?”The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> answered him, “Go, I will deliver them into your hands.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So David and his men went up to Baal Perazim,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10786I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10786I\"></sup> and there he defeated them. He said, “As waters break out, God has broken out against my enemies by my hand.” So that place was called Baal Perazim.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The Philistines had abandoned their gods there, and David gave orders to burn<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10787J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10787J\"></sup> them in the fire.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10787K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10787K\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Once more the Philistines raided the valley;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10788L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10788L\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>so David inquired of God again, and God answered him, “Do not go directly after them, but circle around them and attack them in front of the poplar trees.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>As soon as you hear the sound of marching in the tops of the poplar trees, move out to battle, because that will mean God has gone out in front of you to strike the Philistine army.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So David did as God commanded him, and they struck down the Philistine army, all the way from Gibeon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10791M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10791M\"></sup> to Gezer.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10791N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10791N\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>So David’s fame<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10792O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10792O\"></sup> spread throughout every land, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> made all the nations fear<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10792P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10792P\"></sup> him."
		},
		"15": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">15 </span>After David had constructed buildings for himself in the City of David, he prepared<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10793B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10793B\"></sup> a place for the ark of God and pitched<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10793C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10793C\"></sup> a tent for it.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then David said, “No one but the Levites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10794D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10794D\"></sup> may carry<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10794E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10794E\"></sup> the ark of God, because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> chose them to carry the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and to minister<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10794F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10794F\"></sup> before him forever.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>David assembled all Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10795G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10795G\"></sup> in Jerusalem to bring up the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to the place he had prepared for it.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He called together the descendants of Aaron and the Levites:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10796H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10796H\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>From the descendants of Kohath,Uriel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10797I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10797I\"></sup> the leader and 120 relatives;",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>from the descendants of Merari,Asaiah the leader and 220 relatives;",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>from the descendants of Gershon,Joel the leader and 130 relatives;",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>from the descendants of Elizaphan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10800J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10800J\"></sup>Shemaiah the leader and 200 relatives;",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>from the descendants of Hebron,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10801K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10801K\"></sup>Eliel the leader and 80 relatives;",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>from the descendants of Uzziel,Amminadab the leader and 112 relatives.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then David summoned Zadok<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10803L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10803L\"></sup> and Abiathar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10803M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10803M\"></sup> the priests, and Uriel, Asaiah, Joel, Shemaiah, Eliel and Amminadab the Levites.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He said to them, “You are the heads of the Levitical families; you and your fellow Levites are to consecrate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10804N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10804N\"></sup> yourselves and bring up the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, to the place I have prepared for it.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>It was because you, the Levites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10805O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10805O\"></sup> did not bring it up the first time that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God broke out in anger against us.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10805P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10805P\"></sup> We did not inquire of him about how to do it in the prescribed way.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10805Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10805Q\"></sup>”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So the priests and Levites consecrated themselves in order to bring up the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And the Levites carried the ark of God with the poles on their shoulders, as Moses had commanded<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10807R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10807R\"></sup> in accordance with the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10807S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10807S\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>David<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10808T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10808T\"></sup> told the leaders of the Levites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10808U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10808U\"></sup> to appoint their fellow Levites as musicians<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10808V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10808V\"></sup> to make a joyful sound with musical instruments: lyres, harps and cymbals.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10808W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10808W\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>So the Levites appointed Heman<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10809X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10809X\"></sup> son of Joel; from his relatives, Asaph<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10809Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10809Y\"></sup> son of Berekiah; and from their relatives the Merarites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10809Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10809Z\"></sup> Ethan son of Kushaiah;",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and with them their relatives next in rank: Zechariah, Jaaziel, Shemiramoth, Jehiel, Unni, Eliab, Benaiah, Maaseiah, Mattithiah, Eliphelehu, Mikneiah, Obed-Edom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10810AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10810AA\"></sup> and Jeiel, the gatekeepers.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The musicians Heman,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10811AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10811AB\"></sup> Asaph and Ethan were to sound the bronze cymbals;",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Zechariah, Jaaziel, Shemiramoth, Jehiel, Unni, Eliab, Maaseiah and Benaiah were to play the lyres according to <i>alamoth,</i>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>and Mattithiah, Eliphelehu, Mikneiah, Obed-Edom, Jeiel and Azaziah were to play the harps, directing according to <i>sheminith.</i>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Kenaniah the head Levite was in charge of the singing; that was his responsibility because he was skillful at it.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Berekiah and Elkanah were to be doorkeepers for the ark.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Shebaniah, Joshaphat, Nethanel, Amasai, Zechariah, Benaiah and Eliezer the priests were to blow trumpets<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10816AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10816AC\"></sup> before the ark of God. Obed-Edom and Jehiah were also to be doorkeepers for the ark.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>So David and the elders of Israel and the commanders of units of a thousand went to bring up the ark<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10817AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10817AD\"></sup> of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> from the house of Obed-Edom, with rejoicing.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Because God had helped the Levites who were carrying the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, seven bulls and seven rams<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10818AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10818AE\"></sup> were sacrificed.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Now David was clothed in a robe of fine linen, as were all the Levites who were carrying the ark, and as were the musicians, and Kenaniah, who was in charge of the singing of the choirs. David also wore a linen ephod.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10819AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10819AF\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>So all Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10820AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10820AG\"></sup> brought up the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with shouts,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10820AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10820AH\"></sup> with the sounding of rams’ horns<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10820AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10820AI\"></sup> and trumpets, and of cymbals, and the playing of lyres and harps.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>As the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was entering the City of David, Michal daughter of Saul watched from a window. And when she saw King David dancing and celebrating, she despised him in her heart."
		},
		"16": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">16 </span>They brought the ark of God and set it inside the tent that David had pitched<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10822D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10822D\"></sup> for it, and they presented burnt offerings and fellowship offerings before God.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>After David had finished sacrificing the burnt offerings and fellowship offerings, he blessed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10823E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10823E\"></sup> the people in the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then he gave a loaf of bread, a cake of dates and a cake of raisins<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10824F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10824F\"></sup> to each Israelite man and woman.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He appointed some of the Levites to minister<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10825G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10825G\"></sup> before the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, to extol, thank, and praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel:",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Asaph was the chief, and next to him in rank were Zechariah, then Jaaziel, Shemiramoth, Jehiel, Mattithiah, Eliab, Benaiah, Obed-Edom and Jeiel. They were to play the lyres and harps, Asaph was to sound the cymbals,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>and Benaiah and Jahaziel the priests were to blow the trumpets regularly before the ark of the covenant of God.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>That day David first appointed Asaph and his associates to give praise<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10828H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10828H\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in this manner:",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Give praise<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10829I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10829I\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, proclaim his name;make known among the nations<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10829J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10829J\"></sup> what he has done.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Sing to him, sing praise<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10830K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10830K\"></sup> to him;tell of all his wonderful acts.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Glory in his holy name;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10831L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10831L\"></sup>let the hearts of those who seek the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> rejoice.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Look to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and his strength;seek<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10832M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10832M\"></sup> his face always.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Remember<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10833N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10833N\"></sup> the wonders<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10833O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10833O\"></sup> he has done,his miracles,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10833P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10833P\"></sup> and the judgments he pronounced,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>you his servants, the descendants of Israel,his chosen ones, the children of Jacob.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God;his judgments<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10835Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10835Q\"></sup> are in all the earth.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>He remembers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10836R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10836R\"></sup> his covenant forever,the promise he made, for a thousand generations,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>the covenant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10837S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10837S\"></sup> he made with Abraham,the oath he swore to Isaac.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>He confirmed it to Jacob<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10838T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10838T\"></sup> as a decree,to Israel as an everlasting covenant:",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“To you I will give the land of Canaan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10839U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10839U\"></sup>as the portion you will inherit.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>When they were but few in number,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10840V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10840V\"></sup>few indeed, and strangers in it,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>they wandered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10841W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10841W\"></sup> from nation to nation,from one kingdom to another.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>He allowed no one to oppress them;for their sake he rebuked kings:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10842X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10842X\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“Do not touch my anointed ones;do my prophets<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10843Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10843Y\"></sup> no harm.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Sing to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, all the earth;proclaim his salvation day after day.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Declare his glory<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10845Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10845Z\"></sup> among the nations,his marvelous deeds among all peoples.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>For great is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and most worthy of praise;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10846AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10846AA\"></sup>he is to be feared<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10846AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10846AB\"></sup> above all gods.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10846AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10846AC\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>For all the gods of the nations are idols,but the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> made the heavens.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10847AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10847AD\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Splendor and majesty are before him;strength and joy are in his dwelling place.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Ascribe to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, all you families of nations,ascribe to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> glory and strength.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10849AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10849AE\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Ascribe to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> the glory due his name;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10850AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10850AF\"></sup>bring an offering and come before him.Worship the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in the splendor of his holiness.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10850AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10850AG\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>Tremble<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10851AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10851AH\"></sup> before him, all the earth!The world is firmly established; it cannot be moved.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10851AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10851AI\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Let the heavens rejoice, let the earth be glad;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10852AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10852AJ\"></sup>let them say among the nations, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> reigns!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10852AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10852AK\"></sup>”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Let the sea resound, and all that is in it;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10853AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10853AL\"></sup>let the fields be jubilant, and everything in them!",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Let the trees<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10854AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10854AM\"></sup> of the forest sing,let them sing for joy before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,for he comes to judge<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10854AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10854AN\"></sup> the earth.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Give thanks<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10855AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10855AO\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for he is good;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10855AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10855AP\"></sup>his love endures forever.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10855AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10855AQ\"></sup>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Cry out, “Save us, God our Savior;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10856AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10856AR\"></sup>gather us and deliver us from the nations,that we may give thanks to your holy name,and glory in your praise.”",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Praise be to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10857AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10857AS\"></sup>from everlasting to everlasting.Then all the people said “Amen” and “Praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>David left Asaph and his associates before the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to minister there regularly, according to each day’s requirements.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10858AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10858AT\"></sup>",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>He also left Obed-Edom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10859AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10859AU\"></sup> and his sixty-eight associates to minister with them. Obed-Edom son of Jeduthun, and also Hosah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10859AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10859AV\"></sup> were gatekeepers.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>David left Zadok<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10860AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10860AW\"></sup> the priest and his fellow priests before the tabernacle of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> at the high place in Gibeon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10860AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10860AX\"></sup>",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>to present burnt offerings to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> on the altar of burnt offering regularly, morning and evening, in accordance with everything written in the Law<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10861AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10861AY\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, which he had given Israel.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>With them were Heman<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10862AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10862AZ\"></sup> and Jeduthun and the rest of those chosen and designated by name to give thanks to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “for his love endures forever.”",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Heman and Jeduthun were responsible for the sounding of the trumpets and cymbals and for the playing of the other instruments for sacred song.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10863BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10863BA\"></sup> The sons of Jeduthun<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10863BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10863BB\"></sup> were stationed at the gate.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Then all the people left, each for their own home, and David returned home to bless his family."
		},
		"17": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">17 </span>After David was settled in his palace, he said to Nathan the prophet, “Here I am, living in a house of cedar, while the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is under a tent.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10865B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10865B\"></sup>”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Nathan replied to David, “Whatever you have in mind,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10866C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10866C\"></sup> do it, for God is with you.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But that night the word of God came to Nathan, saying:",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“Go and tell my servant David, ‘This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> says: You<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10868D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10868D\"></sup> are not the one to build me a house to dwell in.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>I have not dwelt in a house from the day I brought Israel up out of Egypt to this day. I have moved from one tent site to another, from one dwelling place to another.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Wherever I have moved with all the Israelites, did I ever say to any of their leaders whom I commanded to shepherd my people, “Why have you not built me a house of cedar?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10870E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10870E\"></sup>”’",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“Now then, tell my servant David, ‘This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> Almighty says: I took you from the pasture, from tending the flock, and appointed you ruler<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10871F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10871F\"></sup> over my people Israel.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>I have been with you wherever you have gone, and I have cut off all your enemies from before you. Now I will make your name like the names of the greatest men on earth.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And I will provide a place for my people Israel and will plant them so that they can have a home of their own and no longer be disturbed. Wicked people will not oppress them anymore, as they did at the beginning",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and have done ever since the time I appointed leaders<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10874G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10874G\"></sup> over my people Israel. I will also subdue all your enemies.“‘I declare to you that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will build a house for you:",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>When your days are over and you go to be with your ancestors, I will raise up your offspring to succeed you, one of your own sons, and I will establish his kingdom.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He is the one who will build<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10876H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10876H\"></sup> a house for me, and I will establish his throne forever.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10876I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10876I\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>I will be his father,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10877J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10877J\"></sup> and he will be my son.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10877K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10877K\"></sup> I will never take my love away from him, as I took it away from your predecessor.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>I will set him over my house and my kingdom forever; his throne<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10878L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10878L\"></sup> will be established forever.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10878M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10878M\"></sup>’”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Nathan reported to David all the words of this entire revelation.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then King David went in and sat before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and he said:“Who am I, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God, and what is my family, that you have brought me this far?",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And as if this were not enough in your sight, my God, you have spoken about the future of the house of your servant. You, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God, have looked on me as though I were the most exalted of men.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“What more can David say to you for honoring your servant? For you know your servant,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. For the sake<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10883O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10883O\"></sup> of your servant and according to your will, you have done this great thing and made known all these great promises.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10883P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10883P\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“There is no one like you, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and there is no God but you,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10884Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10884Q\"></sup> as we have heard with our own ears.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And who is like your people Israel—the one nation on earth whose God went out to redeem<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10885R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10885R\"></sup> a people for himself, and to make a name for yourself, and to perform great and awesome wonders by driving out nations from before your people, whom you redeemed from Egypt?",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>You made your people Israel your very own forever,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10886S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10886S\"></sup> and you, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, have become their God.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“And now, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, let the promise<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10887T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10887T\"></sup> you have made concerning your servant and his house be established forever. Do as you promised,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>so that it will be established and that your name will be great forever. Then people will say, ‘The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> Almighty, the God over Israel, is Israel’s God!’ And the house of your servant David will be established before you.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“You, my God, have revealed to your servant that you will build a house for him. So your servant has found courage to pray to you.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>You, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, are God! You have promised these good things to your servant.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Now you have been pleased to bless the house of your servant, that it may continue forever in your sight;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10891U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10891U\"></sup> for you, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, have blessed it, and it will be blessed forever.”"
		},
		"18": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">18 </span>In the course of time, David defeated the Philistines and subdued them, and he took Gath and its surrounding villages from the control of the Philistines.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>David also defeated the Moabites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10893B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10893B\"></sup> and they became subject to him and brought him tribute.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Moreover, David defeated Hadadezer king of Zobah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10894C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10894C\"></sup> in the vicinity of Hamath, when he went to set up his monument at the Euphrates River.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10894D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10894D\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>David captured a thousand of his chariots, seven thousand charioteers and twenty thousand foot soldiers. He hamstrung<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10895E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10895E\"></sup> all but a hundred of the chariot horses.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When the Arameans of Damascus<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10896F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10896F\"></sup> came to help Hadadezer king of Zobah, David struck down twenty-two thousand of them.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He put garrisons in the Aramean kingdom of Damascus, and the Arameans became subject to him and brought him tribute. The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave David victory wherever he went.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>David took the gold shields carried by the officers of Hadadezer and brought them to Jerusalem.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>From Tebah and Kun, towns that belonged to Hadadezer, David took a great quantity of bronze, which Solomon used to make the bronze Sea,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10899G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10899G\"></sup> the pillars and various bronze articles.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>When Tou king of Hamath heard that David had defeated the entire army of Hadadezer king of Zobah,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>he sent his son Hadoram to King David to greet him and congratulate him on his victory in battle over Hadadezer, who had been at war with Tou. Hadoram brought all kinds of articles of gold, of silver and of bronze.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>King David dedicated these articles to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, as he had done with the silver and gold he had taken from all these nations: Edom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10902H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10902H\"></sup> and Moab, the Ammonites and the Philistines, and Amalek.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10902I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10902I\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Abishai son of Zeruiah struck down eighteen thousand Edomites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10903J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10903J\"></sup> in the Valley of Salt.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>He put garrisons in Edom, and all the Edomites became subject to David. The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave David victory wherever he went.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>David reigned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10905L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10905L\"></sup> over all Israel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10905M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10905M\"></sup> doing what was just and right for all his people.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Joab<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10906N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10906N\"></sup> son of Zeruiah was over the army; Jehoshaphat son of Ahilud was recorder;",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Zadok<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10907O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10907O\"></sup> son of Ahitub and Ahimelek<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10907P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10907P\"></sup> son of Abiathar were priests; Shavsha was secretary;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Benaiah son of Jehoiada was over the Kerethites and Pelethites;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10908Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10908Q\"></sup> and David’s sons were chief officials at the king’s side."
		},
		"19": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">19 </span>In the course of time, Nahash king of the Ammonites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10909B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10909B\"></sup> died, and his son succeeded him as king.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>David thought, “I will show kindness to Hanun son of Nahash, because his father showed kindness to me.” So David sent a delegation to express his sympathy to Hanun concerning his father.When David’s envoys came to Hanun in the land of the Ammonites to express sympathy to him,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>the Ammonite commanders said to Hanun, “Do you think David is honoring your father by sending envoys to you to express sympathy? Haven’t his envoys come to you only to explore and spy out<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10911C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10911C\"></sup> the country and overthrow it?”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So Hanun seized David’s envoys, shaved them, cut off their garments at the buttocks, and sent them away.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When someone came and told David about the men, he sent messengers to meet them, for they were greatly humiliated. The king said, “Stay at Jericho till your beards have grown, and then come back.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When the Ammonites realized that they had become obnoxious<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10914D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10914D\"></sup> to David, Hanun and the Ammonites sent a thousand talents of silver to hire chariots and charioteers from Aram Naharaim, Aram Maakah and Zobah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10914E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10914E\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>They hired thirty-two thousand chariots and charioteers, as well as the king of Maakah with his troops, who came and camped near Medeba,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10915F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10915F\"></sup> while the Ammonites were mustered from their towns and moved out for battle.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>On hearing this, David sent Joab out with the entire army of fighting men.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The Ammonites came out and drew up in battle formation at the entrance to their city, while the kings who had come were by themselves in the open country.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Joab saw that there were battle lines in front of him and behind him; so he selected some of the best troops in Israel and deployed them against the Arameans.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>He put the rest of the men under the command of Abishai<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10919G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10919G\"></sup> his brother, and they were deployed against the Ammonites.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Joab said, “If the Arameans are too strong for me, then you are to rescue me; but if the Ammonites are too strong for you, then I will rescue you.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Be strong, and let us fight bravely for our people and the cities of our God. The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will do what is good in his sight.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then Joab and the troops with him advanced to fight the Arameans, and they fled before him.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When the Ammonites realized that the Arameans were fleeing, they too fled before his brother Abishai and went inside the city. So Joab went back to Jerusalem.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>After the Arameans saw that they had been routed by Israel, they sent messengers and had Arameans brought from beyond the Euphrates River, with Shophak the commander of Hadadezer’s army leading them.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>When David was told of this, he gathered all Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10925H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10925H\"></sup> and crossed the Jordan; he advanced against them and formed his battle lines opposite them. David formed his lines to meet the Arameans in battle, and they fought against him.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But they fled before Israel, and David killed seven thousand of their charioteers and forty thousand of their foot soldiers. He also killed Shophak the commander of their army.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>When the vassals of Hadadezer saw that they had been routed by Israel, they made peace with David and became subject to him.So the Arameans were not willing to help the Ammonites anymore."
		},
		"20": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">20 </span>In the spring, at the time when kings go off to war, Joab led out the armed forces. He laid waste the land of the Ammonites and went to Rabbah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10928B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10928B\"></sup> and besieged it, but David remained in Jerusalem. Joab attacked Rabbah and left it in ruins.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10928C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10928C\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>David took the crown from the head of their king—its weight was found to be a talent of gold, and it was set with precious stones—and it was placed on David’s head. He took a great quantity of plunder from the city",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and brought out the people who were there, consigning them to labor with saws and with iron picks and axes.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10930D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10930D\"></sup> David did this to all the Ammonite towns. Then David and his entire army returned to Jerusalem.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>In the course of time, war broke out with the Philistines, at Gezer.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10931F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10931F\"></sup> At that time Sibbekai the Hushathite killed Sippai, one of the descendants of the Rephaites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10931G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10931G\"></sup> and the Philistines were subjugated.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>In another battle with the Philistines, Elhanan son of Jair killed Lahmi the brother of Goliath the Gittite, who had a spear with a shaft like a weaver’s rod.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10932H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10932H\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>In still another battle, which took place at Gath, there was a huge man with six fingers on each hand and six toes on each foot—twenty-four in all. He also was descended from Rapha.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When he taunted Israel, Jonathan son of Shimea, David’s brother, killed him.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>These were descendants of Rapha in Gath, and they fell at the hands of David and his men."
		},
		"21": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">21 </span>Satan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10936B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10936B\"></sup> rose up against Israel and incited David to take a census<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10936C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10936C\"></sup> of Israel.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So David said to Joab and the commanders of the troops, “Go and count<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10937D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10937D\"></sup> the Israelites from Beersheba to Dan. Then report back to me so that I may know how many there are.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But Joab replied, “May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> multiply his troops a hundred times over.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10938E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10938E\"></sup> My lord the king, are they not all my lord’s subjects? Why does my lord want to do this? Why should he bring guilt on Israel?”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The king’s word, however, overruled Joab; so Joab left and went throughout Israel and then came back to Jerusalem.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Joab reported the number of the fighting men to David: In all Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10940F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10940F\"></sup> there were one million one hundred thousand men who could handle a sword, including four hundred and seventy thousand in Judah.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But Joab did not include Levi and Benjamin in the numbering, because the king’s command was repulsive to him.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>This command was also evil in the sight of God; so he punished Israel.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then David said to God, “I have sinned greatly by doing this. Now, I beg you, take away the guilt of your servant. I have done a very foolish thing.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Gad,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10944G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10944G\"></sup> David’s seer,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10944H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10944H\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“Go and tell David, ‘This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> says: I am giving you three options. Choose one of them for me to carry out against you.’”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So Gad went to David and said to him, “This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> says: ‘Take your choice:",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>three years of famine,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10947I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10947I\"></sup> three months of being swept away before your enemies, with their swords overtaking you, or three days of the sword<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10947J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10947J\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10947K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10947K\"></sup>—days of plague in the land, with the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> ravaging every part of Israel.’ Now then, decide how I should answer the one who sent me.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>David said to Gad, “I am in deep distress. Let me fall into the hands of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for his mercy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10948L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10948L\"></sup> is very great; but do not let me fall into human hands.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sent a plague on Israel, and seventy thousand men of Israel fell dead.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10949M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10949M\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And God sent an angel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10950N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10950N\"></sup> to destroy Jerusalem.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10950O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10950O\"></sup> But as the angel was doing so, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> saw it and relented<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10950P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10950P\"></sup> concerning the disaster and said to the angel who was destroying<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10950Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10950Q\"></sup> the people, “Enough! Withdraw your hand.” The angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was then standing at the threshing floor of Araunah the Jebusite.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>David looked up and saw the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> standing between heaven and earth, with a drawn sword in his hand extended over Jerusalem. Then David and the elders, clothed in sackcloth, fell facedown.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10951R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10951R\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>David said to God, “Was it not I who ordered the fighting men to be counted? I, the shepherd, have sinned and done wrong. These are but sheep.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10952S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10952S\"></sup> What have they done? <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God, let your hand fall on me and my family,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10952T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10952T\"></sup> but do not let this plague remain on your people.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> ordered Gad to tell David to go up and build an altar to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> on the threshing floor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10953U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10953U\"></sup> of Araunah the Jebusite.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So David went up in obedience to the word that Gad had spoken in the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>While Araunah was threshing wheat,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10955V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10955V\"></sup> he turned and saw the angel; his four sons who were with him hid themselves.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then David approached, and when Araunah looked and saw him, he left the threshing floor and bowed down before David with his face to the ground.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>David said to him, “Let me have the site of your threshing floor so I can build an altar to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, that the plague on the people may be stopped. Sell it to me at the full price.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Araunah said to David, “Take it! Let my lord the king do whatever pleases him. Look, I will give the oxen for the burnt offerings, the threshing sledges for the wood, and the wheat for the grain offering. I will give all this.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>But King David replied to Araunah, “No, I insist on paying the full price. I will not take for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> what is yours, or sacrifice a burnt offering that costs me nothing.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>So David paid Araunah six hundred shekels of gold for the site.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>David built an altar to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> there and sacrificed burnt offerings and fellowship offerings. He called on the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> answered him with fire<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10961W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10961W\"></sup> from heaven on the altar of burnt offering.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to the angel, and he put his sword back into its sheath.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>At that time, when David saw that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had answered him on the threshing floor of Araunah the Jebusite, he offered sacrifices there.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>The tabernacle of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, which Moses had made in the wilderness, and the altar of burnt offering were at that time on the high place at Gibeon.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10964X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10964X\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>But David could not go before it to inquire of God, because he was afraid of the sword of the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>."
		},
		"22": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">22 </span>Then David said, “The house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10966A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10966A\"></sup> is to be here, and also the altar of burnt offering for Israel.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So David gave orders to assemble the foreigners<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10967B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10967B\"></sup> residing in Israel, and from among them he appointed stonecutters<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10967C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10967C\"></sup> to prepare dressed stone for building the house of God.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He provided a large amount of iron to make nails for the doors of the gateways and for the fittings, and more bronze than could be weighed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10968D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10968D\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He also provided more cedar logs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10969E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10969E\"></sup> than could be counted, for the Sidonians and Tyrians had brought large numbers of them to David.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>David said, “My son Solomon is young<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10970F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10970F\"></sup> and inexperienced, and the house to be built for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> should be of great magnificence and fame and splendor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10970G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10970G\"></sup> in the sight of all the nations. Therefore I will make preparations for it.” So David made extensive preparations before his death.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then he called for his son Solomon and charged him to build<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10971H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10971H\"></sup> a house for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>David said to Solomon: “My son, I had it in my heart<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10972I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10972I\"></sup> to build<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10972J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10972J\"></sup> a house for the Name<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10972K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10972K\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But this word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to me: ‘You have shed much blood and have fought many wars.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10973L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10973L\"></sup> You are not to build a house for my Name,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10973M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10973M\"></sup> because you have shed much blood on the earth in my sight.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But you will have a son who will be a man of peace<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10974N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10974N\"></sup> and rest,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10974O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10974O\"></sup> and I will give him rest from all his enemies on every side. His name will be Solomon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10974P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10974P\"></sup> and I will grant Israel peace and quiet<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10974Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10974Q\"></sup> during his reign.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>He is the one who will build a house for my Name.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10975R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10975R\"></sup> He will be my son,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10975S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10975S\"></sup> and I will be his father. And I will establish<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10975T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10975T\"></sup> the throne of his kingdom over Israel forever.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10975U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10975U\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“Now, my son, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> be with<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10976V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10976V\"></sup> you, and may you have success and build the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, as he said you would.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> give you discretion and understanding<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10977W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10977W\"></sup> when he puts you in command over Israel, so that you may keep the law of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then you will have success<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10978X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10978X\"></sup> if you are careful to observe the decrees and laws<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10978Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10978Y\"></sup> that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave Moses for Israel. Be strong and courageous.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10978Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10978Z\"></sup> Do not be afraid or discouraged.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“I have taken great pains to provide for the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> a hundred thousand talents of gold, a million talents of silver, quantities of bronze and iron too great to be weighed, and wood and stone. And you may add to them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10979AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10979AA\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>You have many workers: stonecutters, masons and carpenters,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10980AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10980AB\"></sup> as well as those skilled in every kind of work",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>in gold and silver, bronze and iron—craftsmen<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10981AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10981AC\"></sup> beyond number. Now begin the work, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> be with you.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then David ordered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10982AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10982AD\"></sup> all the leaders of Israel to help his son Solomon.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>He said to them, “Is not the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God with you? And has he not granted you rest<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10983AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10983AE\"></sup> on every side?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10983AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10983AF\"></sup> For he has given the inhabitants of the land into my hands, and the land is subject to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and to his people.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Now devote your heart and soul to seeking the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10984AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10984AG\"></sup> Begin to build the sanctuary of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God, so that you may bring the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and the sacred articles belonging to God into the temple that will be built for the Name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”"
		},
		"23": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">23 </span>When David was old and full of years, he made his son Solomon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10985A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10985A\"></sup> king over Israel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10985B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10985B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He also gathered together all the leaders of Israel, as well as the priests and Levites.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The Levites thirty years old or more<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10987C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10987C\"></sup> were counted,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10987D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10987D\"></sup> and the total number of men was thirty-eight thousand.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10987E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10987E\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>David said, “Of these, twenty-four thousand are to be in charge<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10988F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10988F\"></sup> of the work<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10988G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10988G\"></sup> of the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and six thousand are to be officials and judges.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10988H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10988H\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Four thousand are to be gatekeepers and four thousand are to praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with the musical instruments<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10989I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10989I\"></sup> I have provided for that purpose.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10989J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10989J\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>David separated<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10990K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10990K\"></sup> the Levites into divisions corresponding to the sons of Levi:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10990L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10990L\"></sup> Gershon, Kohath and Merari.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Belonging to the Gershonites:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10991M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10991M\"></sup>Ladan and Shimei.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The sons of Ladan:Jehiel the first, Zetham and Joel—three in all.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The sons of Shimei:Shelomoth, Haziel and Haran—three in all.These were the heads of the families of Ladan.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And the sons of Shimei:Jahath, Ziza, Jeush and Beriah.These were the sons of Shimei—four in all.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Jahath was the first and Ziza the second, but Jeush and Beriah did not have many sons; so they were counted as one family with one assignment.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The sons of Kohath:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10996N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10996N\"></sup>Amram, Izhar, Hebron and Uzziel—four in all.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The sons of Amram:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10997O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10997O\"></sup>Aaron and Moses.Aaron was set apart,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10997P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10997P\"></sup> he and his descendants forever, to consecrate the most holy things, to offer sacrifices before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, to minister<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10997Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10997Q\"></sup> before him and to pronounce blessings<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10997R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10997R\"></sup> in his name forever.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The sons of Moses the man<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10998S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10998S\"></sup> of God were counted as part of the tribe of Levi.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The sons of Moses:Gershom and Eliezer.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10999T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10999T\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The descendants of Gershom:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11000U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11000U\"></sup>Shubael was the first.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The descendants of Eliezer:Rehabiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11001V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11001V\"></sup> was the first.Eliezer had no other sons, but the sons of Rehabiah were very numerous.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The sons of Izhar:Shelomith<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11002W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11002W\"></sup> was the first.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The sons of Hebron:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11003X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11003X\"></sup>Jeriah the first, Amariah the second, Jahaziel the third and Jekameam the fourth.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The sons of Uzziel:Micah the first and Ishiah the second.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The sons of Merari:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11005Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11005Y\"></sup>Mahli and Mushi.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11005Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11005Z\"></sup>The sons of Mahli:Eleazar and Kish.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Eleazar died without having sons: he had only daughters. Their cousins, the sons of Kish, married them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11006AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11006AA\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The sons of Mushi:Mahli, Eder and Jerimoth—three in all.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>These were the descendants of Levi by their families—the heads of families as they were registered under their names and counted individually, that is, the workers twenty years old or more<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11008AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11008AB\"></sup> who served in the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>For David had said, “Since the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, has granted rest<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11009AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11009AC\"></sup> to his people and has come to dwell in Jerusalem forever,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>the Levites no longer need to carry the tabernacle or any of the articles used in its service.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11010AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11010AD\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>According to the last instructions of David, the Levites were counted from those twenty years old or more.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>The duty of the Levites was to help Aaron’s descendants in the service of the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>: to be in charge of the courtyards, the side rooms, the purification<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11012AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11012AE\"></sup> of all sacred things and the performance of other duties at the house of God.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>They were in charge of the bread set out on the table,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11013AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11013AF\"></sup> the special flour for the grain offerings,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11013AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11013AG\"></sup> the thin loaves made without yeast, the baking and the mixing, and all measurements of quantity and size.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11013AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11013AH\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>They were also to stand every morning to thank and praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. They were to do the same in the evening<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11014AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11014AI\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>and whenever burnt offerings were presented to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> on the Sabbaths, at the New Moon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11015AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11015AJ\"></sup> feasts and at the appointed festivals.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11015AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11015AK\"></sup> They were to serve before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> regularly in the proper number and in the way prescribed for them.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>And so the Levites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11016AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11016AL\"></sup> carried out their responsibilities for the tent of meeting,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11016AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11016AM\"></sup> for the Holy Place and, under their relatives the descendants of Aaron, for the service of the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11016AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11016AN\"></sup>"
		},
		"24": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">24 </span>These were the divisions<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11017A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11017A\"></sup> of the descendants of Aaron:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11017B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11017B\"></sup>The sons of Aaron were Nadab, Abihu, Eleazar and Ithamar.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11017C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11017C\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>But Nadab and Abihu died before their father did,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11018D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11018D\"></sup> and they had no sons; so Eleazar and Ithamar served as the priests.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>With the help of Zadok<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11019E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11019E\"></sup> a descendant of Eleazar and Ahimelek a descendant of Ithamar, David separated them into divisions for their appointed order of ministering.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>A larger number of leaders were found among Eleazar’s descendants than among Ithamar’s, and they were divided accordingly: sixteen heads of families from Eleazar’s descendants and eight heads of families from Ithamar’s descendants.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>They divided them impartially by casting lots,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11021F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11021F\"></sup> for there were officials of the sanctuary and officials of God among the descendants of both Eleazar and Ithamar.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The scribe Shemaiah son of Nethanel, a Levite, recorded their names in the presence of the king and of the officials: Zadok the priest, Ahimelek<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11022G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11022G\"></sup> son of Abiathar and the heads of families of the priests and of the Levites—one family being taken from Eleazar and then one from Ithamar.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The first lot fell to Jehoiarib,the second to Jedaiah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11023H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11023H\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>the third to Harim,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11024I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11024I\"></sup>the fourth to Seorim,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>the fifth to Malkijah,the sixth to Mijamin,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>the seventh to Hakkoz,the eighth to Abijah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11026J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11026J\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>the ninth to Jeshua,the tenth to Shekaniah,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>the eleventh to Eliashib,the twelfth to Jakim,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>the thirteenth to Huppah,the fourteenth to Jeshebeab,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>the fifteenth to Bilgah,the sixteenth to Immer,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11030K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11030K\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>the seventeenth to Hezir,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11031L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11031L\"></sup>the eighteenth to Happizzez,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>the nineteenth to Pethahiah,the twentieth to Jehezkel,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>the twenty-first to Jakin,the twenty-second to Gamul,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>the twenty-third to Delaiahand the twenty-fourth to Maaziah.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>This was their appointed order of ministering when they entered the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, according to the regulations prescribed for them by their ancestor Aaron, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, had commanded him.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>As for the rest of the descendants of Levi:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11036M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11036M\"></sup>from the sons of Amram: Shubael;from the sons of Shubael: Jehdeiah.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>As for Rehabiah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11037N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11037N\"></sup> from his sons:Ishiah was the first.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>From the Izharites: Shelomoth;from the sons of Shelomoth: Jahath.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The sons of Hebron:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11039O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11039O\"></sup> Jeriah the first, Amariah the second, Jahaziel the third and Jekameam the fourth.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The son of Uzziel: Micah;from the sons of Micah: Shamir.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>The brother of Micah: Ishiah;from the sons of Ishiah: Zechariah.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The sons of Merari:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11042P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11042P\"></sup> Mahli and Mushi.The son of Jaaziah: Beno.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The sons of Merari:from Jaaziah: Beno, Shoham, Zakkur and Ibri.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>From Mahli: Eleazar, who had no sons.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>From Kish: the son of Kish:Jerahmeel.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And the sons of Mushi: Mahli, Eder and Jerimoth.These were the Levites, according to their families.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>They also cast lots,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11047Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11047Q\"></sup> just as their relatives the descendants of Aaron did, in the presence of King David and of Zadok, Ahimelek, and the heads of families of the priests and of the Levites. The families of the oldest brother were treated the same as those of the youngest."
		},
		"25": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">25 </span>David, together with the commanders of the army, set apart some of the sons of Asaph,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11048A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11048A\"></sup> Heman<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11048B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11048B\"></sup> and Jeduthun<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11048C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11048C\"></sup> for the ministry of prophesying,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11048D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11048D\"></sup> accompanied by harps, lyres and cymbals.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11048E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11048E\"></sup> Here is the list of the men<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11048F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11048F\"></sup> who performed this service:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11048G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11048G\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>From the sons of Asaph:Zakkur, Joseph, Nethaniah and Asarelah. The sons of Asaph were under the supervision of Asaph, who prophesied under the king’s supervision.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>As for Jeduthun, from his sons:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11050H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11050H\"></sup>Gedaliah, Zeri, Jeshaiah, Shimei, Hashabiah and Mattithiah, six in all, under the supervision of their father Jeduthun, who prophesied, using the harp<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11050I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11050I\"></sup> in thanking and praising the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>As for Heman, from his sons:Bukkiah, Mattaniah, Uzziel, Shubael and Jerimoth; Hananiah, Hanani, Eliathah, Giddalti and Romamti-Ezer; Joshbekashah, Mallothi, Hothir and Mahazioth.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>(All these were sons of Heman the king’s seer. They were given him through the promises of God to exalt him. God gave Heman fourteen sons and three daughters.)",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>All these men were under the supervision of their father<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11053J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11053J\"></sup> for the music of the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, with cymbals, lyres and harps, for the ministry at the house of God.Asaph, Jeduthun and Heman<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11053K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11053K\"></sup> were under the supervision of the king.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11053L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11053L\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Along with their relatives—all of them trained and skilled in music for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>—they numbered 288.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Young and old alike, teacher as well as student, cast lots<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11055M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11055M\"></sup> for their duties."
		},
		"26": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">26 </span>The divisions of the gatekeepers:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11079A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11079A\"></sup>From the Korahites: Meshelemiah son of Kore, one of the sons of Asaph.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Meshelemiah had sons:Zechariah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11080B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11080B\"></sup> the firstborn,Jediael the second,Zebadiah the third,Jathniel the fourth,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Elam the fifth,Jehohanan the sixthand Eliehoenai the seventh.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Obed-Edom also had sons:Shemaiah the firstborn,Jehozabad the second,Joah the third,Sakar the fourth,Nethanel the fifth,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Ammiel the sixth,Issachar the seventhand Peullethai the eighth.(For God had blessed Obed-Edom.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11083C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11083C\"></sup>)",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Obed-Edom’s son Shemaiah also had sons, who were leaders in their father’s family because they were very capable men.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The sons of Shemaiah: Othni, Rephael, Obed and Elzabad; his relatives Elihu and Semakiah were also able men.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>All these were descendants of Obed-Edom; they and their sons and their relatives were capable men with the strength to do the work—descendants of Obed-Edom, 62 in all.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Meshelemiah had sons and relatives, who were able men—18 in all.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Hosah the Merarite had sons: Shimri the first (although he was not the firstborn, his father had appointed him the first),<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11088D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11088D\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Hilkiah the second, Tabaliah the third and Zechariah the fourth. The sons and relatives of Hosah were 13 in all.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>These divisions of the gatekeepers, through their leaders, had duties for ministering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11090E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11090E\"></sup> in the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, just as their relatives had.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Lots<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11091F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11091F\"></sup> were cast for each gate, according to their families, young and old alike.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The lot for the East Gate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11092G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11092G\"></sup> fell to Shelemiah. Then lots were cast for his son Zechariah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11092H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11092H\"></sup> a wise counselor, and the lot for the North Gate fell to him.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The lot for the South Gate fell to Obed-Edom,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11093I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11093I\"></sup> and the lot for the storehouse fell to his sons.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The lots for the West Gate and the Shalleketh Gate on the upper road fell to Shuppim and Hosah.Guard was alongside of guard:",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>There were six Levites a day on the east, four a day on the north, four a day on the south and two at a time at the storehouse.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>As for the court to the west, there were four at the road and two at the court itself.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>These were the divisions of the gatekeepers who were descendants of Korah and Merari.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11097J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11097J\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Their fellow Levites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11098K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11098K\"></sup> were in charge of the treasuries of the house of God and the treasuries for the dedicated things.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11098L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11098L\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The descendants of Ladan, who were Gershonites through Ladan and who were heads of families belonging to Ladan the Gershonite,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11099M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11099M\"></sup> were Jehieli,",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>the sons of Jehieli, Zetham and his brother Joel. They were in charge of the treasuries<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11100N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11100N\"></sup> of the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>From the Amramites, the Izharites, the Hebronites and the Uzzielites:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11101O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11101O\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Shubael,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11102P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11102P\"></sup> a descendant of Gershom son of Moses, was the official in charge of the treasuries.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>His relatives through Eliezer: Rehabiah his son, Jeshaiah his son, Joram his son, Zikri his son and Shelomith<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11103Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11103Q\"></sup> his son.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Shelomith and his relatives were in charge of all the treasuries for the things dedicated<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11104R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11104R\"></sup> by King David, by the heads of families who were the commanders of thousands and commanders of hundreds, and by the other army commanders.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Some of the plunder taken in battle they dedicated for the repair of the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And everything dedicated by Samuel the seer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11106S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11106S\"></sup> and by Saul son of Kish, Abner son of Ner and Joab son of Zeruiah, and all the other dedicated things were in the care of Shelomith and his relatives.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>From the Izharites: Kenaniah and his sons were assigned duties away from the temple, as officials and judges<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11107T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11107T\"></sup> over Israel.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>From the Hebronites: Hashabiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11108U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11108U\"></sup> and his relatives—seventeen hundred able men—were responsible in Israel west of the Jordan for all the work of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and for the king’s service.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>As for the Hebronites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11109V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11109V\"></sup> Jeriah was their chief according to the genealogical records of their families. In the fortieth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11109W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11109W\"></sup> year of David’s reign a search was made in the records, and capable men among the Hebronites were found at Jazer in Gilead.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Jeriah had twenty-seven hundred relatives, who were able men and heads of families, and King David put them in charge of the Reubenites, the Gadites and the half-tribe of Manasseh for every matter pertaining to God and for the affairs of the king."
		},
		"27": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">27 </span>This is the list of the Israelites—heads of families, commanders of thousands and commanders of hundreds, and their officers, who served the king in all that concerned the army divisions that were on duty month by month throughout the year. Each division consisted of 24,000 men.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>In charge of the first division, for the first month, was Jashobeam<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11112A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11112A\"></sup> son of Zabdiel. There were 24,000 men in his division.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He was a descendant of Perez and chief of all the army officers for the first month.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>In charge of the division for the second month was Dodai<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11114B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11114B\"></sup> the Ahohite; Mikloth was the leader of his division. There were 24,000 men in his division.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The third army commander, for the third month, was Benaiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11115C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11115C\"></sup> son of Jehoiada the priest. He was chief and there were 24,000 men in his division.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>This was the Benaiah who was a mighty warrior among the Thirty and was over the Thirty. His son Ammizabad was in charge of his division.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The fourth, for the fourth month, was Asahel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11117D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11117D\"></sup> the brother of Joab; his son Zebadiah was his successor. There were 24,000 men in his division.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The fifth, for the fifth month, was the commander Shamhuth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11118E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11118E\"></sup> the Izrahite. There were 24,000 men in his division.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The sixth, for the sixth month, was Ira<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11119F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11119F\"></sup> the son of Ikkesh the Tekoite. There were 24,000 men in his division.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The seventh, for the seventh month, was Helez<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11120G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11120G\"></sup> the Pelonite, an Ephraimite. There were 24,000 men in his division.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The eighth, for the eighth month, was Sibbekai<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11121H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11121H\"></sup> the Hushathite, a Zerahite. There were 24,000 men in his division.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The ninth, for the ninth month, was Abiezer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11122I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11122I\"></sup> the Anathothite, a Benjamite. There were 24,000 men in his division.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The tenth, for the tenth month, was Maharai<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11123J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11123J\"></sup> the Netophathite, a Zerahite. There were 24,000 men in his division.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The eleventh, for the eleventh month, was Benaiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11124K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11124K\"></sup> the Pirathonite, an Ephraimite. There were 24,000 men in his division.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The twelfth, for the twelfth month, was Heldai<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11125L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11125L\"></sup> the Netophathite, from the family of Othniel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11125M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11125M\"></sup> There were 24,000 men in his division.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The leaders of the tribes of Israel:over the Reubenites: Eliezer son of Zikri;over the Simeonites: Shephatiah son of Maakah;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>over Levi: Hashabiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11127N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11127N\"></sup> son of Kemuel;over Aaron: Zadok;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11127O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11127O\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>over Judah: Elihu, a brother of David;over Issachar: Omri son of Michael;",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>over Zebulun: Ishmaiah son of Obadiah;over Naphtali: Jerimoth son of Azriel;",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>over the Ephraimites: Hoshea son of Azaziah;over half the tribe of Manasseh: Joel son of Pedaiah;",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>over the half-tribe of Manasseh in Gilead: Iddo son of Zechariah;over Benjamin: Jaasiel son of Abner;",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>over Dan: Azarel son of Jeroham.These were the leaders of the tribes of Israel.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>David did not take the number of the men twenty years old or less,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11133P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11133P\"></sup> because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had promised to make Israel as numerous as the stars<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11133Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11133Q\"></sup> in the sky.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Joab son of Zeruiah began to count the men but did not finish. God’s wrath came on Israel on account of this numbering,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11134R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11134R\"></sup> and the number was not entered in the book of the annals of King David.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Azmaveth son of Adiel was in charge of the royal storehouses.Jonathan son of Uzziah was in charge of the storehouses in the outlying districts, in the towns, the villages and the watchtowers.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Ezri son of Kelub was in charge of the workers who farmed the land.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Shimei the Ramathite was in charge of the vineyards.Zabdi the Shiphmite was in charge of the produce of the vineyards for the wine vats.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Baal-Hanan the Gederite was in charge of the olive and sycamore-fig<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11138S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11138S\"></sup> trees in the western foothills.Joash was in charge of the supplies of olive oil.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Shitrai the Sharonite was in charge of the herds grazing in Sharon.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11139T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11139T\"></sup>Shaphat son of Adlai was in charge of the herds in the valleys.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Obil the Ishmaelite was in charge of the camels.Jehdeiah the Meronothite was in charge of the donkeys.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Jaziz the Hagrite<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11141U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11141U\"></sup> was in charge of the flocks.All these were the officials in charge of King David’s property.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Jonathan, David’s uncle, was a counselor, a man of insight and a scribe. Jehiel son of Hakmoni took care of the king’s sons.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Ahithophel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11143V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11143V\"></sup> was the king’s counselor.Hushai<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11143W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11143W\"></sup> the Arkite was the king’s confidant.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Ahithophel was succeeded by Jehoiada son of Benaiah and by Abiathar.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11144X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11144X\"></sup>Joab<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11144Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11144Y\"></sup> was the commander of the royal army."
		},
		"28": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">28 </span>David summoned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11145A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11145A\"></sup> all the officials<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11145B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11145B\"></sup> of Israel to assemble at Jerusalem: the officers over the tribes, the commanders of the divisions in the service of the king, the commanders of thousands and commanders of hundreds, and the officials in charge of all the property and livestock belonging to the king and his sons, together with the palace officials, the warriors and all the brave fighting men.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>King David rose to his feet and said: “Listen to me, my fellow Israelites, my people. I had it in my heart<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11146C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11146C\"></sup> to build a house as a place of rest<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11146D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11146D\"></sup> for the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for the footstool<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11146E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11146E\"></sup> of our God, and I made plans to build it.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11146F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11146F\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But God said to me,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11147G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11147G\"></sup> ‘You are not to build a house for my Name,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11147H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11147H\"></sup> because you are a warrior and have shed blood.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11147I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11147I\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“Yet the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, chose me<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11148J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11148J\"></sup> from my whole family<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11148K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11148K\"></sup> to be king over Israel forever. He chose Judah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11148L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11148L\"></sup> as leader, and from the tribe of Judah he chose my family, and from my father’s sons he was pleased to make me king over all Israel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11148M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11148M\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Of all my sons—and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has given me many<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11149N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11149N\"></sup>—he has chosen my son Solomon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11149O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11149O\"></sup> to sit on the throne<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11149P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11149P\"></sup> of the kingdom of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> over Israel.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He said to me: ‘Solomon your son is the one who will build<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11150Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11150Q\"></sup> my house and my courts, for I have chosen him to be my son,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11150R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11150R\"></sup> and I will be his father.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>I will establish his kingdom forever if he is unswerving in carrying out my commands and laws,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11151S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11151S\"></sup> as is being done at this time.’",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“So now I charge you in the sight of all Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11152T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11152T\"></sup> and of the assembly of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and in the hearing of our God: Be careful to follow all the commands<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11152U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11152U\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, that you may possess this good land and pass it on as an inheritance to your descendants forever.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11152V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11152V\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“And you, my son Solomon, acknowledge the God of your father, and serve him with wholehearted devotion<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11153W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11153W\"></sup> and with a willing mind, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> searches every heart<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11153X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11153X\"></sup> and understands every desire and every thought. If you seek him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11153Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11153Y\"></sup> he will be found by you; but if you forsake<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11153Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11153Z\"></sup> him, he will reject<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11153AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11153AA\"></sup> you forever.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Consider now, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has chosen you to build a house as the sanctuary. Be strong and do the work.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then David gave his son Solomon the plans<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11155AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11155AB\"></sup> for the portico of the temple, its buildings, its storerooms, its upper parts, its inner rooms and the place of atonement.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He gave him the plans of all that the Spirit<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11156AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11156AC\"></sup> had put in his mind for the courts of the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and all the surrounding rooms, for the treasuries of the temple of God and for the treasuries for the dedicated things.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11156AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11156AD\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>He gave him instructions for the divisions<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11157AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11157AE\"></sup> of the priests and Levites, and for all the work of serving in the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, as well as for all the articles to be used in its service.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He designated the weight of gold for all the gold articles to be used in various kinds of service, and the weight of silver for all the silver articles to be used in various kinds of service:",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>the weight of gold for the gold lampstands<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11159AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11159AF\"></sup> and their lamps, with the weight for each lampstand and its lamps; and the weight of silver for each silver lampstand and its lamps, according to the use of each lampstand;",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>the weight of gold for each table<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11160AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11160AG\"></sup> for consecrated bread; the weight of silver for the silver tables;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>the weight of pure gold for the forks, sprinkling bowls<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11161AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11161AH\"></sup> and pitchers; the weight of gold for each gold dish; the weight of silver for each silver dish;",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and the weight of the refined gold for the altar of incense.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11162AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11162AI\"></sup> He also gave him the plan for the chariot,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11162AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11162AJ\"></sup> that is, the cherubim of gold that spread their wings and overshadow<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11162AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11162AK\"></sup> the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“All this,” David said, “I have in writing as a result of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s hand on me, and he enabled me to understand all the details<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11163AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11163AL\"></sup> of the plan.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11163AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11163AM\"></sup>”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>David also said to Solomon his son, “Be strong and courageous,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11164AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11164AN\"></sup> and do the work. Do not be afraid or discouraged, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God, my God, is with you. He will not fail you or forsake<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11164AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11164AO\"></sup> you until all the work for the service of the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is finished.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11164AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11164AP\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The divisions of the priests and Levites are ready for all the work on the temple of God, and every willing person skilled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11165AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11165AQ\"></sup> in any craft will help you in all the work. The officials and all the people will obey your every command.”"
		},
		"29": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">29 </span>Then King David said to the whole assembly: “My son Solomon, the one whom God has chosen, is young and inexperienced.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11166A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11166A\"></sup> The task is great, because this palatial structure is not for man but for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>With all my resources I have provided for the temple of my God—gold<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11167B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11167B\"></sup> for the gold work, silver for the silver, bronze for the bronze, iron for the iron and wood for the wood, as well as onyx for the settings, turquoise,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11167C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11167C\"></sup> stones of various colors, and all kinds of fine stone and marble—all of these in large quantities.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11167D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11167D\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Besides, in my devotion to the temple of my God I now give my personal treasures of gold and silver for the temple of my God, over and above everything I have provided<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11168E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11168E\"></sup> for this holy temple:",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>three thousand talents of gold (gold of Ophir)<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11169F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11169F\"></sup> and seven thousand talents of refined silver,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11169G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11169G\"></sup> for the overlaying of the walls of the buildings,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>for the gold work and the silver work, and for all the work to be done by the craftsmen. Now, who is willing to consecrate themselves to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> today?”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then the leaders of families, the officers of the tribes of Israel, the commanders of thousands and commanders of hundreds, and the officials<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11171H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11171H\"></sup> in charge of the king’s work gave willingly.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11171I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11171I\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>They<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11172J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11172J\"></sup> gave toward the work on the temple of God five thousand talents and ten thousand darics of gold, ten thousand talents of silver, eighteen thousand talents of bronze and a hundred thousand talents of iron.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Anyone who had precious stones<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11173K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11173K\"></sup> gave them to the treasury of the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in the custody of Jehiel the Gershonite.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11173L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11173L\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The people rejoiced at the willing response of their leaders, for they had given freely and wholeheartedly<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11174M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11174M\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. David the king also rejoiced greatly.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>David praised the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in the presence of the whole assembly, saying,“Praise be to you, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,the God of our father Israel,from everlasting to everlasting.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Yours, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, is the greatness and the power<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11176N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11176N\"></sup>and the glory and the majesty and the splendor,for everything in heaven and earth is yours.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11176O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11176O\"></sup>Yours, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, is the kingdom;you are exalted as head over all.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11176P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11176P\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Wealth and honor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11177Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11177Q\"></sup> come from you;you are the ruler<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11177R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11177R\"></sup> of all things.In your hands are strength and powerto exalt and give strength to all.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Now, our God, we give you thanks,and praise your glorious name.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“But who am I, and who are my people, that we should be able to give as generously as this?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11179S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11179S\"></sup> Everything comes from you, and we have given you only what comes from your hand.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11179T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11179T\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>We are foreigners and strangers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11180U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11180U\"></sup> in your sight, as were all our ancestors. Our days on earth are like a shadow,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11180V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11180V\"></sup> without hope.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God, all this abundance that we have provided for building you a temple for your Holy Name comes from your hand, and all of it belongs to you.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>I know, my God, that you test the heart<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11182W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11182W\"></sup> and are pleased with integrity. All these things I have given willingly and with honest intent. And now I have seen with joy how willingly your people who are here have given to you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11182X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11182X\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of our fathers Abraham, Isaac and Israel, keep these desires and thoughts in the hearts of your people forever, and keep their hearts loyal to you.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And give my son Solomon the wholehearted devotion<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11184Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11184Y\"></sup> to keep your commands, statutes and decrees<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11184Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11184Z\"></sup> and to do everything to build the palatial structure for which I have provided.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11184AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11184AA\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then David said to the whole assembly, “Praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.” So they all praised the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of their fathers; they bowed down, prostrating themselves before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and the king.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The next day they made sacrifices to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and presented burnt offerings to him:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11186AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11186AC\"></sup> a thousand bulls, a thousand rams and a thousand male lambs, together with their drink offerings, and other sacrifices in abundance for all Israel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11186AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11186AD\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>They ate and drank with great joy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11187AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11187AE\"></sup> in the presence of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that day.Then they acknowledged Solomon son of David as king a second time, anointing him before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to be ruler and Zadok<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11187AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11187AF\"></sup> to be priest.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>So Solomon sat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11188AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11188AG\"></sup> on the throne<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11188AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11188AH\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> as king in place of his father David. He prospered and all Israel obeyed him.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>All the officers and warriors, as well as all of King David’s sons,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11189AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11189AI\"></sup> pledged their submission to King Solomon.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> highly exalted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11190AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11190AJ\"></sup> Solomon in the sight of all Israel and bestowed on him royal splendor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11190AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11190AK\"></sup> such as no king over Israel ever had before.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11190AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11190AL\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>David son of Jesse was king<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11191AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11191AN\"></sup> over all Israel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11191AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11191AO\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>He ruled over Israel forty years—seven in Hebron<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11192AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11192AP\"></sup> and thirty-three in Jerusalem.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11192AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11192AQ\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>He died<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11193AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11193AR\"></sup> at a good old age, having enjoyed long life, wealth and honor. His son Solomon succeeded him as king.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11193AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11193AS\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>As for the events of King David’s reign, from beginning to end, they are written in the records of Samuel the seer,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11194AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11194AT\"></sup> the records of Nathan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11194AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11194AU\"></sup> the prophet and the records of Gad<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11194AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11194AV\"></sup> the seer,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>together with the details of his reign and power, and the circumstances that surrounded him and Israel and the kingdoms of all the other lands."
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;